<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse eesm&auml;rk </eesti>
<inglise>Purpose of Act </inglise>
<eesti>Kohaliku omavalitsuse korralduse seadus m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;lesanded, vastutuse ja korralduse ning omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste suhted omavahel ja riigiorganitega. </eesti>
<inglise>The Local Government Organisation Act determines the functions, responsibility and organisation of local government and the relations of local governments with one another and with state bodies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohaliku omavalitsuse m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of local government </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohalik omavalitsus on p&otilde;hiseaduses s&auml;testatud omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse - valla v&otilde;i linna - demokraatlikult moodustatud v&otilde;imuorganite &otilde;igus, v&otilde;ime ja kohustus seaduste alusel iseseisvalt korraldada ja juhtida kohalikku elu, l&auml;htudes valla- v&otilde;i linnaelanike &otilde;igustatud vajadustest ja huvidest ning arvestades valla v&otilde;i linna arengu ise&auml;rasusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Local government is the right, authority and duty of the democratically formed bodies of power of a local government provided for in the Constitution, a rural municipality or city, to independently organise and manage local issues pursuant to law and based on the legitimate needs and interests of the residents of the rural municipality or city, and considering the specific development of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohalik omavalitsus: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Local government is: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rajaneb riigi territooriumi haldusjaotusel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) based on the division of the territory of the state into administrative units; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teostub demokraatlikult moodustatud esindus- ja v&otilde;imuorganite kaudu, samuti kohaliku elu k&uuml;simustes rahvak&uuml;sitluse v&otilde;i rahvaalgatuse teel. </eesti>
<inglise>2) exercised by democratically formed legislative and executive bodies and, with regard to local issues, by means of opinion polls or public initiative. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohaliku omavalitsuse p&otilde;him&otilde;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Principles of local government </inglise>
<eesti>Kohalik omavalitsus rajaneb j&auml;rgmistel p&otilde;him&otilde;tetel: </eesti>
<inglise>Local government is based on the following principles: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kohaliku elu k&uuml;simuste iseseisev ja l&otilde;plik otsustamine ja korraldamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the independent and final resolution of local issues, and organisation thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) iga&uuml;he seaduslike &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste kohustuslik tagamine vallas ja linnas; </eesti>
<inglise>2) mandatory guarantee of everyone's lawful rights and freedoms in the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>3) seaduste j&auml;rgimine oma &uuml;lesannete ja kohustuste t&auml;itmisel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) observance of law in the performance of functions and duties; </inglise>
<eesti>4) valla- ja linnaelanike &otilde;igus osaleda kohaliku omavalitsuse teostamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the right of the residents of a rural municipality or city to participate in the exercise of local government; </inglise>
<eesti>5) vastutus oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise eest; </eesti>
<inglise>5) responsibility for the performance of functions; </inglise>
<eesti>6) tegevuse avalikkus; </eesti>
<inglise>6) transparency of activities; </inglise>
<eesti>7) avalike teenuste osutamine soodsaimatel tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>7) provision of public services under the most favourable terms. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsusorganid </eesti>
<inglise>Local government bodies </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsusorganid on: </eesti>
<inglise>Local government bodies are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) volikogu - kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse esinduskogu, mis valitakse valla v&otilde;i linna h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguslike elanike poolt kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu valimise seaduse alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the council - the legislative body of a local government elected by the residents of the rural municipality or city with the right to vote pursuant to the Local Government Council Election Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) valitsus - volikogu poolt moodustatav t&auml;itevorgan. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the government - the executive body formed by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Valla ja linna eelarve ning &otilde;igus kehtestada makse ja panna peale koormisi </eesti>
<inglise>Rural municipality or city budget and right to impose taxes and duties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vallal ja linnal on k&auml;esolevast seadusest ja eelarve- ning maksuseadustest l&auml;htuv iseseisev eelarve. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Rural municipalities and cities have independent budgets pursuant to this Act and legislation concerning budgets and taxation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogul on seaduse alusel &otilde;igus kehtestada makse ja panna peale koormisi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Councils have the right to impose taxes and duties pursuant to law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse &uuml;lesanded ja p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Functions and competence of local governments </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse &uuml;lesandeks on korraldada antud vallas v&otilde;i linnas sotsiaalabi ja -teenuseid, vanurite hoolekannet, noorsoot&ouml;&ouml;d, elamu- ja kommunaalmajandust, veevarustust ja kanalisatsiooni, heakorda, territoriaalplaneerimist, valla- v&otilde;i linnasisest &uuml;histransporti ning valla teede ja linnat&auml;navate korrashoidu, juhul kui need &uuml;lesanded ei ole seadusega antud kellegi teise t&auml;ita. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The functions of a local government include the organisation, in the rural municipality or city, of social assistance and services, welfare services for the elderly, youth work, housing and utilities, the supply of water and sewerage, the provision of public services and amenities, physical planning, public transportation within the rural municipality or city, and the maintenance of rural municipality roads and city streets unless such functions are assigned by law to other persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 392) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 27, 392) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse &uuml;lesandeks on korraldada antud vallas v&otilde;i linnas koolieelsete lasteasutuste, p&otilde;hikoolide, g&uuml;mnaasiumide ja huvialakoolide, raamatukogude, rahvamajade, muuseumide, spordibaaside, turva- ja hooldekodude, tervishoiuasutuste ning teiste kohalike asutuste &uuml;lalpidamist, juhul kui need on omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse omanduses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The functions of a local government include the organisation, in the rural municipality or city, of the maintenance of pre-school child care institutions, basic schools, secondary schools, hobby schools, libraries, community centres, museums, sports facilities, shelters, care homes, health care institutions and other local agencies if such agencies are in the ownership of the local government. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud asutuste osas v&otilde;idakse seadusega ette n&auml;ha teatud kulude katmist kas riigieelarvest v&otilde;i muudest allikatest. </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of specified expenses of such agencies from the state budget or other sources may be prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.02.94 j&otilde;ust.11.03.94 - RT I 1994, 12, 200) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.02.94 entered into force 11.03.94 - RT I 1994, 12, 200) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. ja 2.l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud &uuml;lesannetele otsustab ja korraldab omavalitsus&uuml;ksus neid kohaliku elu k&uuml;simusi: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In addition to the functions provided for in subsections (1) and (2) of this section, local governments resolve and organise local issues: </inglise>
<eesti>1) mis on talle pandud teiste seadustega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) which are assigned to them by other Acts; </inglise>
<eesti>2) mis ei ole seadusega antud kellegi teise otsustada ja korraldada. </eesti>
<inglise>2) which are not assigned by law to other persons for resolution and organisation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksus t&auml;idab riiklikke kohustusi: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Local governments fulfil state functions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) mis on talle pandud seadusega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) which are assigned to them by law; </inglise>
<eesti>2) mis tulenevad selleks volitatud riigiorgani ja antud volikogu vahelisest lepingust. </eesti>
<inglise>2) which arise from a contract between an authorised state body and a specific council. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 4.l&otilde;ike punkti 1 alusel kohalikule omavalitsusele pandud kohustustega seotud kulud kaetakse riigieelarvest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Expenses incurred in the performance of functions assigned to a local government pursuant to clause (4) 1) of this section shall be covered from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu ja valitsuse &otilde;igusaktid </eesti>
<inglise>Council and government legislation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogul ja valitsusel on &otilde;igus anda &uuml;ldaktidena m&auml;&auml;rusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Councils and governments have the right to issue regulations as legislation of general application. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogul on &otilde;igus &uuml;ksikaktidena vastu v&otilde;tta otsuseid, valitsusel anda korraldusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Councils have the right to pass resolutions and governments have the right to pass orders as legislation of specific application. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Volikogu ja valitsuse &otilde;igusaktid kehtivad antud omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse haldusterritooriumil. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Legislation passed by a council or government is valid in the administrative territory of the local government. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Valla ja linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rus </eesti>
<inglise>Statutes of rural municipality or city </inglise>
<eesti>Valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rus on &otilde;igusakt, milles s&auml;testatakse antud valla v&otilde;i linna omavalitsusorganite, nende komisjonide ning valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuste moodustamise kord, &otilde;igused, kohustused ja t&ouml;&ouml;kord. </eesti>
<inglise>The statutes of a rural municipality or city are legislation which provide the procedure for the formation, rights, duties and rules of procedure of the local government bodies, their committees and agencies in the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Arengukava </eesti>
<inglise>Development plan </inglise>
<eesti>Valla v&otilde;i linna arengukava on dokument, mis sisaldab antud omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse majandusliku ja sotsiaalse olukorra ning keskkonnaseisundi anal&uuml;&uuml;si, pikemaajalise tegevuse kavandamise ning edasise arengu suundi ja eelistusi. </eesti>
<inglise>The development plan of a rural municipality or city is a document which provides an analysis concerning the economic and social situation, environmental condition, and trends and preferences for planning the long-term activity and further development of the local government. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Vald ja linn avalik-&otilde;igusliku isikuna </eesti>
<inglise>Rural municipalities and cities as persons in public law </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Nii vald kui ka linn on avalik-&otilde;iguslik isik, keda esindavad seaduste ja omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse alusel ning kehtestatud korras oma p&auml;devuse piires volikogu, volikogu esimees, valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus ning vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Rural municipalities and cities are persons in public law, which are represented by the council, the chairman of the council, the rural municipality or city government and the rural municipality or city mayor, within the limits of their competence, on the basis of Acts, the statutes of the local government and pursuant to the established procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vallal ja linnal on avalik-&otilde;igusliku isikuna iseseisev eelarve, arveldusarve pangas ja oma s&uuml;mboolika. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Rural municipalities and cities as persons in public law have independent budgets, bank accounts and insignia. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Maakogu </eesti>
<inglise>County Assembly </inglise>
<eesti>(Kehtetu - 23.11.94 j&otilde;ust.12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </eesti>
<inglise>(Repealed - 23.11.94 entered into force 12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste &otilde;igus moodustada liite ja &uuml;hisasutusi </eesti>
<inglise>Right of local governments to form associations and joint agencies </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksustel on &otilde;igus moodustada teiste omavalitsus&uuml;ksustega liite ja &uuml;hisasutusi &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Local governments have the right to form associations and joint agencies with other local governments on the bases of and pursuant to the procedure provided for in legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse &otilde;igus osaleda rahvusvahelistes organisatsioonides </eesti>
<inglise>Right of local governments to participate in international organisations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksusel on &otilde;igus astuda vastavate rahvus- vaheliste organisatsioonide liikmeks v&otilde;i arendada nendega koost&ouml;&ouml;d. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Local governments have the right to become members of corresponding international organisations and to co-operate with such organisations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Suhetes rahvusvaheliste organisatsioonidega esindab omavalitsus&uuml;ksust tema volikogu v&otilde;i viimase poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud esindus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In relations with international organisations, a local government is represented by the council or representatives appointed by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse vapp ja lipp </eesti>
<inglise>Coats of arms and flag of local government </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksusel v&otilde;ivad olla oma vapp ja lipp, mis kuuluvad koosk&otilde;lastamisele, kinnitamisele ja registreerimisele vastavalt seadusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A local government may have a coat of arms and a flag which shall be concorded, approved and registered pursuant to law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vapi ja lipu kasutamine s&auml;testatakse seadusega ning valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The use of the coat of arms and flag shall be provided by an Act and the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse lipp ei tohi normaalm&otilde;&otilde;tmetelt olla suurem riigilipust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The standard dimensions of the flag of a local government shall not exceed the dimensions of the national flag. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse &otilde;iguste kaitse </eesti>
<inglise>Protection of rights of local governments </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksust likvideerida v&otilde;i selle piire v&otilde;i nime muuta ei tohi ilma antud valla v&otilde;i linna volikogu arvamust &auml;ra kuulamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A local government shall not be liquidated and its boundaries or name shall not be altered without hearing the opinion of the council of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogul on &otilde;igus antud omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse territooriumil korraldada olulistes k&uuml;simustes elanike k&uuml;sitlusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A council has the right to organise opinion polls concerning essential issues among the residents of the territory of the local government. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksusel on oma seaduslike &otilde;iguste kaitseks v&otilde;i vaidluste lahendamiseks &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Local governments have the right of recourse to the courts for the protection of their lawful rights and for the resolution of disputes. </inglise>
<eesti>II peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu </eesti>
<inglise>Council </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu moodustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formation of council </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu valitakse kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu valimise seaduse alusel &uuml;ldistel, &uuml;hetaolistel ja otsestel valimistel kolmeks aastaks, kusjuures h&auml;&auml;letamine on salajane. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Councils are elected by general, uniform and direct elections by secret ballot for a term of three years pursuant to the Local Government Council Election Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogu liikmete arvu m&auml;&auml;rab volikogu eelmine koosseis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The number of members of a council is determined by the previous membership of the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Volikogus peab olema v&auml;hemalt 7 liiget. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A council shall have at least seven members. </inglise>
<eesti>Liikmete arv m&auml;&auml;ratakse valla- v&otilde;i linnaelanike arvust l&auml;htudes valimiste aasta 1.jaanuari seisuga j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>The number of members of a council is determined based on the number of residents in the rural municipality or city as of 1 January of the election year as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;le 2000 elaniku, v&auml;hemalt 13-liikmeline volikogu; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a council of not less than 13 members for more than 2000 residents; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;le 5000 elaniku, v&auml;hemalt 17-liikmeline volikogu; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a council of not less than 17 members for more than 5 000 residents; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;le 10000 elaniku, v&auml;hemalt 21-liimeline volikogu; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a council of not less than 21 members for more than 10 000 residents; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;le 50000 elaniku, v&auml;hemalt 31-liikmeline volikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a council of not less than 31 members for more than 50 000 residents; </inglise>
<eesti>(3 (1)) Kui valimised toimuvad kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuste &uuml;hinemise t&otilde;ttu, m&auml;&auml;ratakse valitava volikogu liikmete arv &uuml;hinemisel moodustatud valla v&otilde;i linna elanike arvust l&auml;htuvalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3 (1)) If elections are held due to the merger of local governments, the number of members of the council to be elected is determined based on the number of residents in the rural municipality or city formed by the merger. </inglise>
<eesti>(25.02.98 j&otilde;ust.30.03.98 - RT I 1998, 28, 356) </eesti>
<inglise>(25.02.98 entered into force 30.03.98 - RT I 1998, 28, 356) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Volikogu uue koosseisu ja tema liikmete volitused algavad ning volikogu eelmise koosseisu ja tema liikmete volitused l&otilde;pevad valimistulemuste v&auml;ljakuulutamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The authority of the new membership of a council and of its members commences, and the authority of the previous membership of the council and of its members terminates, as of the date the election results are announced. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu liige </eesti>
<inglise>Council member </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu liige on isik, kes on osutunud valituks vastavalt kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu valimise seadusele (RT I 1996, 37, 739; RT I 1999, 60, 618; 2001, 95, 588). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A council member is a person who is elected in accordance with the Local Government Council Election Act (RT I 1996, 37, 739; RT I 1999, 60, 618; 2001, 95, 588). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogu liige juhindub seadusest, valla v&otilde;i linna &otilde;igusaktidest ning valla- v&otilde;i linnaelanike vajadustest ja huvidest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Council members shall operate pursuant to law, rural municipality or city legislation and the needs and interests of the residents of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Volikogul on &otilde;igus maksta oma liikmetele h&uuml;vitust volikogu &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel tehtud kulutuste ning p&otilde;hit&ouml;&ouml;kohal saamata j&auml;&auml;nud t&ouml;&ouml;tasu eest volikogu kehtestatud m&auml;&auml;ras ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A council has the right to compensate its members for expenses incurred in the performance of tasks assigned to them by the council and for unreceived remuneration in their principal jobs pursuant to the rates and procedure established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Volikogu esimehe v&otilde;i &uuml;he volikogu aseesimehe ametikoht v&otilde;ib volikogu otsusel olla palgaline. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The position of chairman of the council and deputy chairman may be remunerative based on a resolution of the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Volikogu liige ei tohi osa v&otilde;tta volikogu sellise &uuml;ksikakti arutamisest ja otsustamisest, mille suhtes on tal huvide konflikt vastavalt korruptsioonivastase seaduse (RT I 1999, 16, 276; 87, 791; 2000, 25, 145; 2001, 58, 357) paragrahv 25 l&otilde;ikele 1. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A council member shall not participate in the debate and resolution of legislation of specific application with regard to which he or she has a conflict of interest pursuant to subsection 25 (1) of the Anti-corruption Act (RT I 1999, 16, 276; 87, 791; 2000, 25, 145; 2001, 58, 357). </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud juhul on volikogu liige kohustatud enne k&uuml;simuse arutelu algust tegema avalduse enda mitteosalemise kohta antud p&auml;evakorrapunkti arutamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) In the case provided for in subsection (5) of this section, a council member is required to make a statement concerning his or her non-participation in the discussion of such item prior to the commencement of the debate of the items on the order of business. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastav m&auml;rge fikseeritakse volikogu istungi protokollis. </eesti>
<inglise>A corresponding notation is documented in the minutes of the council session. </inglise>
<eesti>K&uuml;simuste arutamiseks ja otsustamiseks vajalik kvoorum on selle volikogu liikme v&otilde;rra v&auml;iksem. </eesti>
<inglise>The quorum necessary for the debate and resolution of items shall be decreased by such council member. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Volikogu liige on kohustatud esitama majanduslike huvide deklaratsiooni korruptsioonivastases seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A council member is required to submit a declaration of economic interests pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Anti-corruption Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu liikme volituste ennet&auml;htaegne l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Premature termination of authority of council member </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu liikme volitused l&otilde;pevad enne t&auml;htaega seoses: </eesti>
<inglise>The authority of a council member terminates prematurely due to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) volikogu tegutsemisv&otilde;imetusega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the inability of the council to act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tagasiastumisega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the resignation of the council member; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&auml;ljalangemisega Eesti h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguslike kodanike riiklikust registrist antud vallas v&otilde;i linnas; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the withdrawal of the council member from the Estonian Electoral Register of Citizens in the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>4) nimetamisega kohtunikuks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the appointment of the council member as a judge; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tahtliku kuriteo eest s&uuml;&uuml;dim&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumisega; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the entry into force of a conviction against the council member for an intentional criminal offence; </inglise>
<eesti>6) j&otilde;ustunud kohtuotsusega, millega t&uuml;histati valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjoni otsus tema registreerimise kohta volikogu liikmeks; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the annulment by a court of a resolution of the rural municipality or city election committee concerning the registration of the council member; </inglise>
<eesti>7) teov&otilde;imetuks tunnistamisega; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the divestment of the council member of active legal capacity; </inglise>
<eesti>8) surmaga. </eesti>
<inglise>8) the death of the council member. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r saadab hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 1 s&auml;testatud asjaolude teatavaks saamisest vastava teate valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Not later than within three working days after the circumstances provided for in clause (1) 1) of this section become known, the rural municipality or city secretary shall forward a corresponding notice to the rural municipality or city election committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 2 s&auml;testatud juhul esitab volikogu liige vastava avalduse valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;rile, kes saadab selle hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;ttesaamisest arvates valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the case provided for in clause (1) 2) of this section, the council member shall submit a corresponding application to the rural municipality or city secretary who shall forward the application to the rural municipality or city election committee not later than within three working days after the receipt of the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r saadab hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 3, 4 ja 8 s&auml;testatud asjaolude teatavaks saamisest vastava teate valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Not later than within three working days after the circumstances provided for in clauses (1) 3), 4) and 8) of this section become known, the rural municipality or city secretary shall forward a corresponding notice to the rural municipality or city election committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 5-7 s&auml;testatud juhtudel saadab valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r vastava kohtuotsuse hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul selle k&auml;ttesaamisest arvates valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the cases provided for in clauses (1) 5) -7) of this section, the rural municipality or city secretary shall forward the corresponding court judgment to the rural municipality or city election committee not later than within three working days after the receipt of the judgment. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705; 27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705; 27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu liikme volituste peatumine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of authority of council member </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu liikme volituste peatumine t&auml;hendab volikogu liikme ajutist vabanemist volikogu liikme &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>The suspension of the authority of a council member means the temporary release of the council member from the performance of the functions of a council member. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogu liikme volitused peatuvad: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The authority of a council member is suspended due to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valimisega Vabariigi Presidendiks, nimetamisega Vabariigi Valitsuse liikmeks, riigisekret&auml;riks, riigikontrol&ouml;riks, &otilde;iguskantsleriks v&otilde;i maavanemaks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the election of the council member to the office of the President of the Republic, the appointment of the council member as a member of the Government of the Republic, the State Secretary, the Auditor General, the Legal Chancellor or a county governor; </inglise>
<eesti>2) nimetamisega prokur&ouml;riks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the appointment of the council member as a prosecutor; </inglise>
<eesti>3) valimisega vallavanemaks v&otilde;i linnapeaks, kinnitamisega valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse liikmeks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the election of the council member to the post of rural municipality or city mayor or confirmation of his or her appointment as a member of the rural municipality or city government; </inglise>
<eesti>4) nimetamisega valla- v&otilde;i linnaametnikuks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the appointment of the council member as a rural municipality or city official; </inglise>
<eesti>5) asumisega tegevteenistusse kaitsev&auml;es v&otilde;i sellega v&otilde;rdsustatud teenistuses; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the entrance of the council member into active service in the armed forces or service equal thereto; </inglise>
<eesti>6) tema suhtes t&otilde;kendina vahi alla v&otilde;tmise kohaldamisega &uuml;le kolme kuu; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the placement of the council member in preventive detention for more than three months; </inglise>
<eesti>7) t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete, &otilde;pingute t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;i muul p&otilde;hjusel, mis takistab volikogu istungitel osalemist v&auml;hemalt kolme j&auml;rjestikuse kuu ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>7) duties, studies or any other reasons which hinder the council member's participation in the council sessions during at least three consecutive months. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ike punktis 3 s&auml;testatud piirang ei kehti volikogu uude koosseisu valitud eelmise koosseisu vallavanema, linnapea ja valitsuse liikmete suhtes, kes on esitanud lahkumispalve, kuid j&auml;tkavad oma tegevust kuni volikogu poolt uue valitsuse kinnitamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The restriction provided for in clause (2) 3) of this section does not apply to rural municipality or city mayors and government members of the previous membership who are elected to the new membership of the council and have submitted their but continue their activity until the council confirms the membership of the new government. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ike punktides 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud asjaolusid kinnitava dokumendi saamisel, kuid mitte hiljem kui kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast Riigi Teatajas avaldamist saadab valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r vastava teate valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon the receipt of a document certifying the circumstances provided for in clauses (2) 1) or 2) of this section and not later than within three working days of the publication of such document in the Riigi Teataja, the rural municipality or city secretary shall forward a corresponding notice to the rural municipality or city election committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ike punktis 4 s&auml;testatud juhul saadab valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast vastava korralduse vastuv&otilde;tmist selle valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the case provided for in clause (2) 4) of this section, the rural municipality or city secretary shall forward a corresponding order to the rural municipality or city election committee not later than within three working days after the passage thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ike punktides 5 ja 7 s&auml;testatud juhtudel saadab valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r vastava avalduse hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) In the cases provided for in clauses (2) 5) and 7) of this section, the rural municipality or city secretary shall forward a corresponding application to the rural municipality or city election committee not later than within three working days. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ike punktis 6 s&auml;testatud juhul saadab valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast vastava kohtum&auml;&auml;ruse k&auml;ttesaamist selle valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) In the case provided for in clause (2) 6) of this section, the rural municipality or city secretary shall forward the corresponding court ruling to the rural municipality or city election committee not later than within three working days after the receipt thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705; 27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705; 27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu asendusliige </eesti>
<inglise>Alternate council member </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 18 ja 19 s&auml;testatud juhtudel astub volikogu liikme asemele volikogu asendusliige. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the cases provided for in &sect;&sect; 18 and 19 of this Act, an alternate council member shall replace a council member. </inglise>
<eesti>Asendusliige m&auml;&auml;ratakse valimiskomisjoni otsusega valimiskomisjoni kinnitatud asendusliikmete nimekirja alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>An alternate council member shall be designated by a resolution of the electoral committee on the basis of a list of alternate members approved by the electoral committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogu liikme volitused l&otilde;pevad enne t&auml;htaega k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 18 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The authority of a council member shall terminate prematurely in the cases provided for in subsection 18 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Asendusliikme volitused volikogu liikmena algavad valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjoni otsuse j&otilde;ustumise hetkest. </eesti>
<inglise>The authority of an alternative council member shall commence upon the entry into force of the resolution of the rural municipality or city election committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Volikogu liikme volitused peatuvad ning asendusliikme volitused volikogu liikmena algavad valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjoni otsuse j&otilde;ustumise hetkest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The authority of the member of the local government council is suspended, and the authority of the alternate member as council member commences upon the entry into force of the decision of the rural municipality or city election committee. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu liikme volituste peatumine ja asendusliikme m&auml;&auml;ramine vormistatakse &uuml;he otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The suspension of the authority of the member of the local government council and the designation of an alternate council member shall be formulated as a single resolution. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjon teeb &sect;-des 18, 19 ja 20 (1) etten&auml;htud otsused viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast vastava otsuse aluseks oleva dokumendi k&auml;ttesaamist ja saadab need viivitamata valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;rile. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A rural municipality or city election committee shall make the resolutions prescribed in &sect;&sect;18, 19 and 20 (1) within five working days as of the receipt of the document which was the basis of the corresponding resolution and shall promptly send them to the rural municipality or city secretary. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjon on valitud volikogu liikme registreerimisel teadlik sellest, et k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 18 1. l&otilde;ikes v&otilde;i &sect; 19 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud asjaolude t&otilde;ttu volikogu liige ei saa volikogu t&ouml;&ouml;s osaleda v&otilde;i on esitanud loobumisavalduse, m&auml;&auml;rab valimiskomisjon tema asemele kohe asendusliikme. </eesti>
<inglise>If upon the registration of an elected member of the council, the rural municipality or city election committee is aware that the council member is unable to participate in the work of the council or has submitted an application for declination due to the circumstances provided for in subsection 18 (1) or 19 (2) of this Act, the election committee shall immediately replace such council member by an alternate member. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Volikogu liikme volituste ennet&auml;htaegsel l&otilde;ppemisel v&otilde;i peatumisel saab volikogu liikmeks esimene sama erakonna v&otilde;i valimisliidu valimata j&auml;&auml;nud kandidaat, kes kandideeris samas valimisringkonnas, milles kandideeris asendatav volikogu liige. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the premature termination or suspension of the authority of a council member, the new council member shall be the first candidate who was not elected of the same political party or election coalition and who ran as a candidate in the same electoral district as the council member to be replaced. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui esimene asendusliige loobub v&otilde;i ei saa volikogu t&ouml;&ouml;s osaleda k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 18 1. l&otilde;ikes v&otilde;i &sect; 19 2. l&otilde;ikes m&auml;rgitud p&otilde;hjustel, saab volikogu liikmeks j&auml;rgmine sama erakonna v&otilde;i valimisliidu samas valimisringkonnas valimata j&auml;&auml;nud kandidaat. </eesti>
<inglise>If the first alternate council member declines or is unable to participate in the work of the council due to the reasons specified in subsection 18 (1) or 19 (2) of this Act, the new council member shall be the next candidate who was not elected of the same political party or election coalition and who ran as a candidate in the same electoral district. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui asendusliige teatab kirjalikult oma loobumisest v&otilde;i ei saa volikogu t&ouml;&ouml;s osaleda k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 18 1. l&otilde;ikes m&auml;rgitud p&otilde;hjustel, kaotab asendusliige oma koha asendusliikmete nimekirjas. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An alternate council member who notifies of his or her declination in writing or is unable to participate in the work of the council due to the reasons specified in subsection 18 (1) of this Act shall be deleted from the list of alternate members. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui esimene asendusliige ei saa volikogu t&ouml;&ouml;s osaleda k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 19 2. l&otilde;ikes m&auml;rgitud p&otilde;hjustel, j&auml;&auml;b esimene asendusliige asendusliikmete nimekirja. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) An alternate council member ranking first in the list of alternate members who is unable to participate in the work of the council due to the reasons specified in subsection 19 (2) of this Act shall not be deleted from the list of alternate members. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Kui asendatav volikogu liige kandideeris &uuml;ksikkandidaadina v&otilde;i kui selles valimisringkonnas samal erakonnal v&otilde;i valimisliidul rohkem asendusliikmeid ei ole, saab volikogu liikmeks asendusliige, kes on m&auml;&auml;ratud erakondade ja valimisliitude vahel jaotatud lisamandaadi alusel, mille on registreerinud valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjon. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) If the member to be replaced ran as an independent candidate or if the same political party or election coalition has no more alternate members in the electoral district, an alternate member designated on the basis of an additional mandate distributed among the political parties and election coalitions and registered by the rural municipality or city election committee shall become a member of the council. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui selles valimisringkonnas &uuml;helgi erakonnal v&otilde;i valimisliidul rohkem asendusliikmeid ei ole, saab volikogu liikmeks selles valimisringkonnas valimata j&auml;&auml;nud kandidaatidest k&otilde;ige rohkem h&auml;&auml;li saanud kandidaat. </eesti>
<inglise>If the political parties or election coalitions have no more alternate members in the electoral district, the unelected candidate who received the largest number of votes in the electoral district shall be the council member. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Kui valimisringkonna kandidaatide koondnimekirjas on ainult &uuml;ksikkandidaadid, on volikogu liikmeks esimene samas valimisringkonnas valimata j&auml;&auml;nud &uuml;ksikkandidaat. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) If only independent candidates are in the consolidated list of candidates in an electoral district, the council member shall be the first unelected independent candidate who ran as candidate in the electoral district. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui esimene valimata j&auml;&auml;nud &uuml;ksikkandidaat loobub v&otilde;i tema volitused l&otilde;pevad v&otilde;i peatuvad, on volikogu liikmeks j&auml;rgmine valimata j&auml;&auml;nud &uuml;ksikkandidaat. </eesti>
<inglise>If the first unelected independent candidate declines or his or her authority terminates or is suspended, the next unelected independent candidate shall be the council member. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Kui &uuml;ksikkandidaat teatab kirjalikult oma loobumisest v&otilde;i ei saa volikogu t&ouml;&ouml;s osaleda k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 18 1. l&otilde;ikes m&auml;rgitud p&otilde;hjustel, ei saa teda hiljem enam volikogu liikmeks m&auml;&auml;rata. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) If an independent candidate notifies of his or her declination in writing or is unable to participate in the work of the council due to the reasons specified in subsection 18 (1) of this Act, he or she can no longer be designated as council member. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu liikme volituste taastumine </eesti>
<inglise>Restoration of authority of council member </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu liikme volituste taastumiseks esitab ta vastava avalduse valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;rile, kes saadab selle hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a council member wants his or her authority to be restored, the council member shall submit a corresponding application to the rural municipality or city secretary who shall forward the application to the rural municipality or city election committee not later than within three working days. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogu liikme volituste taastumisel l&otilde;pevad selle asendusliikme volitused, kes on viimasena m&auml;&auml;ratud asendama lisamandaadi alusel v&otilde;i samas erakonnas v&otilde;i valimisliidus kandideerinud volikogu liiget sellest valimisringkonnast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon restoration of the authority of a council member, the authority of the alternate council member who was last designated to replace a council member on the basis of an additional mandate or from among the candidates of the same political party or election coalition in the electoral district, shall terminate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui valimisringkonna kandidaatide koondnimekirjas on ainult &uuml;ksikkandidaadid, l&otilde;pevad volikogu liikme volituste taastumisel selle volikogu liikme volitused, kes on viimasena m&auml;&auml;ratud asendama volikogu liiget sellest valimisringkonnast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If only independent candidates are in the consolidated list of candidates in an electoral district, then upon restoration of the authority of a council member, the authority of the council member who was last designated to replace the council member in the electoral district, shall terminate. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Volikogu liikme volitused taastuvad ja teda asendanud volikogu liikme volitused l&otilde;pevad valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjoni otsuse j&otilde;ustumise hetkest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The authority of the member of the local government council is restored, and the authority of the council member replacing him or her is terminated upon the entry into force of the resolution of the rural municipality or city election committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. (Kehtetu - 16.05.96 j&otilde;ust.08.06.96 - RT I 1996, 37, 739) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. (Repealed - 16.05.96 entered into force 08.06.96 - RT I 1996, 37, 739) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of council </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu ainup&auml;devusse kuulub j&auml;rgmiste k&uuml;simuste otsustamine: </eesti>
<inglise>Resolution of the following issues is within the exclusive competence of a council: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valla- v&otilde;i linnaeelarve vastuv&otilde;tmine ja muutmine ning selle t&auml;itmise aruande kinnitamine ning audiitori m&auml;&auml;ramine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the passage and amendment of the rural municipality or city budgets, approval of reports on the implementation thereof and appointment of auditors; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kohalike maksude kehtestamine, muutmine ja kehtetuks tunnistamine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the imposition, amendment and invalidation of local taxes; </inglise>
<eesti>3) valla v&otilde;i linna eelarvesse laekuvate kohalike maksude puhul soodustuste andmise korra kehtestamine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the establishment of the procedure for the grant of tax incentives concerning local taxes which accrue to the rural municipality or city budget; </inglise>
<eesti>4) koormiste m&auml;&auml;ramine; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the imposition of duties; </inglise>
<eesti>5) toetuste andmise ja valla v&otilde;i linna eelarvest finantseeritavate teenuste osutamise korra kehtestamine; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the establishment of the procedure for the grant of benefits and for the provision of services financed from the rural municipality or city budget; </inglise>
<eesti>6) valla- v&otilde;i linnavara valitsemise, kasutamise ja k&auml;sutamise korra kehtestamine; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the establishment of the procedure for the possession, use and disposal of municipal property; </inglise>
<eesti>7) valla v&otilde;i linna arengukava vastuv&otilde;tmine ja muutmine; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the approval and amendment of the rural municipality or city development plans; </inglise>
<eesti>8) laenude ja teiste varaliste kohustuste v&otilde;tmine; </eesti>
<inglise>8) the taking of loans and assumption of other proprietary obligations; </inglise>
<eesti>9) valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitamine, muutmine ja kehtetuks tunnistamine; </eesti>
<inglise>9) the approval, amendment and repeal of the statutes of the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>10) taotluse esitamine v&otilde;i arvamuse andmine valla v&otilde;i linna piiride v&otilde;i valla v&otilde;i linna nime muutmiseks ning sellega seotud varaliste v&otilde;i muude vaidluste lahendamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>10) the submission of requests or provision of opinions concerning the alteration of boundaries of the rural municipality or city, or the change of name of the rural municipality or city, and the settlement of proprietary or other disputes pertaining thereto; </inglise>
<eesti>11) osavalla ja linnaosa moodustamine ja l&otilde;petamine, tema p&auml;devuse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramine ja p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitamine; </eesti>
<inglise>11) the formation and liquidation of rural municipality or city districts, and determination of the competence and approval of the statutes thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>12) volikogu j&auml;rgmise koosseisu liikmete arvu m&auml;&auml;ramine; </eesti>
<inglise>12) the determination of the number of members of the next membership of the council; </inglise>
<eesti>13) valimisringkondade arvu, piiride ja &uuml;htse numeratsiooni ning igas valimisringkonnas mandaatide arvu m&auml;&auml;ramine, valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjoni ja jaoskonnakomisjoni moodustamine; </eesti>
<inglise>13) the determination of the number, boundaries and common numeration of electoral districts, determination of the number of mandates in each electoral district, and the formation of the rural municipality or city election committee and division committees; </inglise>
<eesti>14) volikogu esimehe, aseesimehe v&otilde;i aseesimeeste valimine; </eesti>
<inglise>14) the election of the chairman, deputy chairman or deputy chairmen of the council; </inglise>
<eesti>15) vallavanema v&otilde;i linnapea valimine ja ametist vabastamine; </eesti>
<inglise>15) the election and release from office of the rural municipality or city mayor; </inglise>
<eesti>16) valitsuse liikmete arvu ja valitsuse struktuuri kinnitamine; </eesti>
<inglise>16) the approval of the number of members of the government and structure thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>17) valitsuse liikmete kinnitamine ja nende vabastamine valitsuse liikmete kohustustest ning palgaliste valitsusliikmete ametisse nimetamine ja ametist vabastamine; </eesti>
<inglise>17) the confirmation of the appointment to and release from office of the members of the rural municipality or city government, and the appointment to and release from remunerative positions of members of the government; </inglise>
<eesti>18) umbusalduse avaldamine volikogu esimehele, volikogu aseesimehele, volikogu komisjoni esimehele, volikogu komisjoni aseesimehele, revisjonikomisjoni liikmele, valitsusele, vallavanemale v&otilde;i linnapeale v&otilde;i valitsuse liikmele; </eesti>
<inglise>18) the expression of no confidence in the chairman of the council, the deputy chairman of the council, a chairman of a council committee, a deputy chairman of a council committee, a member of the audit committee, the government, the rural municipality or city mayor, or a member of the government; </inglise>
<eesti>19) vallavanemale v&otilde;i linnapeale ja palgalistele valitsusliikmetele t&ouml;&ouml;tasu m&auml;&auml;ramine ning teistele valitsusliikmetele h&uuml;vituse maksmise otsustamine ja selle suuruse m&auml;&auml;ramine; </eesti>
<inglise>19) the determination of remuneration to the rural municipality or city mayor and members of the government working in remunerative positions, and the resolution on payment of compensation to other members of the government and the determination of the amount of compensation to be paid; </inglise>
<eesti>20) volikogu komisjonide moodustamine ja tegevuse l&otilde;petamine, nende esimeeste ja aseesimeeste valimine volikogu liikmete hulgast ja komisjonide koosseisu kinnitamine; </eesti>
<inglise>20) the formation and liquidation of council committees, election of chairmen and deputy chairmen thereto from among council members, and approval of the membership of such committees; </inglise>
<eesti>21) volikogu esimehele v&otilde;i &uuml;hele aseesimehele t&ouml;&ouml;tasu v&otilde;i h&uuml;vituse m&auml;&auml;ramine v&otilde;i aseesimeestele h&uuml;vituse m&auml;&auml;ramine; </eesti>
<inglise>21) the determination of the remuneration or compensation of the chairman and one of his or her deputies, and the determination of the compensation of the deputy chairmen; </inglise>
<eesti>22) volikogu liikmetele volikogu &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisel tehtud kulutuste ning volikogu t&ouml;&ouml;st osav&otilde;tu eest h&uuml;vituse suuruse ja maksmise korra kehtestamine; </eesti>
<inglise>22) the determination of the amount and procedure for payment of compensation paid to council members for expenses incurred in the performance of tasks assigned to them by the council and for the participation in the work of the council; </inglise>
<eesti>23) valla v&otilde;i linna esindamise korra kehtestamine; </eesti>
<inglise>23) the establishment of the procedure for representation of the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>24) valla v&otilde;i linna poolt &auml;ri&uuml;hingu ja sihtasutuse asutamine, l&otilde;petamine ning p&otilde;hikirja kinnitamine ja muutmine; </eesti>
<inglise>24) the foundation and dissolution of companies and foundations by the rural municipality or city, and the approval and amendment of the articles of association of such companies and foundations; </inglise>
<eesti>25) valla v&otilde;i linna osalemise otsustamine &auml;ri&uuml;hingus, sihtasutuses, mittetulundus&uuml;hingus ning nendes osalemise l&otilde;petamise otsustamine; </eesti>
<inglise>25) the resolution of the participation and termination of participation of the rural municipality or city in a company, foundation or non-profit association; </inglise>
<eesti>26) kohtukaasistujate valimine; </eesti>
<inglise>26) the election of lay judges; </inglise>
<eesti>27) Vabariigi Presidendi valimiskogusse volikogu esindaja v&otilde;i esindajate valimine; </eesti>
<inglise>27) the election of a representative or representatives of the council to the electoral body of the President of the Republic; </inglise>
<eesti>28) maavanema kandidatuuri koosk&otilde;lastamiseks volikogu esindaja valimine; </eesti>
<inglise>28) the election of a representative of the council for the concordance of the candidature of a county governor; </inglise>
<eesti>29) valla v&otilde;i linna ehitusm&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitamine, muutmine ja t&uuml;histamine; </eesti>
<inglise>29) the approval, amendment or repeal of the rural municipality or city building regulation; </inglise>
<eesti>30) kinnisasja sundv&otilde;&otilde;randamise taotluse esitamine; </eesti>
<inglise>30) the submission of applications for the expropriation of immovables; </inglise>
<eesti>31) &uuml;ldplaneeringu algatamine, kehtestamine ja t&uuml;histamine; </eesti>
<inglise>31) the initiation, adoption and repeal of comprehensive plans; </inglise>
<eesti>32) &uuml;ldplaneeringu projekti vastuv&otilde;tmine ja avaliku v&auml;ljapaneku v&auml;ljakuulutamine; </eesti>
<inglise>32) the acceptance of draft comprehensive plans and notification of the public display thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>33) detailplaneeringu kehtestamine ja t&uuml;histamine; </eesti>
<inglise>33) the adoption and repeal of detailed plans; </inglise>
<eesti>34) valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuse ja valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuse hallatava asutuse moodustamine, &uuml;mberkorraldamine ja tegevuse l&otilde;petamine ning ametiasutuse p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitamine; </eesti>
<inglise>34) the foundation and restructuring of rural municipality or city administrative agencies and agencies under the administration of rural municipality or city administrative agencies, and the termination of the operation and the approval of the statutes of such agencies; </inglise>
<eesti>35) valla- v&otilde;i linnaametnikele sotsiaalsete garantiide kehtestamine; </eesti>
<inglise>35) the establishment of social guarantees for rural municipality or city officials; </inglise>
<eesti>36) valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuste struktuuri ja teenistujate koosseisu ning palgam&auml;&auml;rade ja palgatingimuste kinnitamine; </eesti>
<inglise>36) the approval of the structure of rural municipality or city administrative agencies, of the composition of their staff of public servants, salary rates and wage conditions; </inglise>
<eesti>37) muud seadusega volikogu ainup&auml;devusse antud k&uuml;simused. </eesti>
<inglise>37) other issues placed within the exclusive competence of the council by law. </inglise>
<eesti>Seadusega kohaliku omavalitsuse, kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsusorgani p&auml;devusse antud k&uuml;simusi otsustab kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu, kes v&otilde;ib delegeerida nende k&uuml;simuste lahendamise valitsusele. (3) Kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu v&otilde;ib delegeerida valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele muudatuste tegemise aasta jooksul ametiasutuste struktuuris ja teenistujate koosseisus volikogu poolt kinnitatud teenistujate &uuml;ldarvu ja palgafondi piires. </eesti>
<inglise>The issues placed within the competence of local government shall be resolved by the local government council who has the right to delegate the resolution of such issues to the government. (3) A local government council may delegate to a rural municipality or city government the right to make changes during a year in the structure of administrative agencies and the staff of public servants employed by the administrative agencies in so far as such changes are carried out considering the limits set by the total number of public servants and the salary fund. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu &otilde;igusaktidele esitatavad n&otilde;uded ja &otilde;igusaktide j&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for council legislation and entry into force thereof </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu &otilde;igusaktid avalikustatakse valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Council legislation shall be disclosed pursuant to the procedure provided for in the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti, loetakse volikogu m&auml;&auml;rus avalikustatuks p&auml;rast tema v&auml;ljapanekut valla- v&otilde;i linnakantseleis. </eesti>
<inglise>A council regulation is deemed to be disclosed after the display thereof in the rural municipality or city office unless the statutes of the rural municipality or city provide otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu m&auml;&auml;rused j&otilde;ustuvad kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast nende avalikustamist, kui &otilde;igusaktis eneses ei ole s&auml;testatud hilisemat j&otilde;ustumise t&auml;htaega. </eesti>
<inglise>A council regulation enters into force on the third day after being made public unless a later date is provided for in the regulation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) M&auml;&auml;ruses ei saa kehtestada tagasiulatuvalt s&auml;tteid, mis toovad kaasa isikute kohustuste ja vastutuse suurenemise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Provisions by which the obligations or responsibility of persons is retroactively increased shall not be established by a regulation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Volikogu otsused j&otilde;ustuvad neis s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajal ning need tuleb saata t&auml;itjatele ja asjaosalistele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A council resolution enters into force on the date provided for therein and shall be forwarded to the person who shall execute such resolutions and to other persons concerned. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Volikogu m&auml;&auml;rustele ja otsustele kirjutab alla volikogu esimees v&otilde;i tema asendaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Council regulations and resolutions shall be signed by the chairman of the council or his or her deputy. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Volikogu m&auml;&auml;rused ja otsused ning istungite protokollid peavad olema seaduses ja valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras k&auml;ttesaadavad k&otilde;igile isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Council regulations and resolutions and minutes of council sessions shall be accessible to everyone pursuant to the procedure provided by law and the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) &Uuml;ldist t&auml;htsust omavad volikogu m&auml;&auml;rused saadetakse Riigikantseleile avaldamiseks kinnitatud &auml;rakirjana nii paberkandjal kui elektroonilisel kujul Riigikantselei poolt antud tehniliste juhiste kohaselt n&auml;dala jooksul p&auml;rast aktile allakirjutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Certified copies on paper and in electronic form of council regulations of general importance shall be sent for publication to the State Chancellery pursuant to technical instructions provided by the State Chancellery within a week after signing the instrument. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Volikogu m&auml;&auml;rused ja otsused ning istungite protokollid vormistatakse ja avalikustatakse eesti keeles. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Council regulations and resolutions and minutes of council sessions shall be prepared and made public in Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksustes, mille p&uuml;sielanike enamiku keel ei ole eesti keel, v&otilde;idakse volikogu istungite protokollid lisaks eesti keelele vormistada ka selle omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse p&uuml;sielanike enamiku moodustava v&auml;hemusrahvuse keeles. </eesti>
<inglise>In a local government where the majority of permanent residents are non-Estonian speakers, minutes of council sessions may, in addition to Estonian language, be also prepared in the language of the national minority constituting the majority of the permanent residents of the local government. </inglise>
<eesti>(04.12.2001 j&otilde;ust.21.10.2002 - RT I 2001, 100, 642) </eesti>
<inglise>(04.12.2001 entered into force 21.10.2002 - RT I 2001, 100, 642) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igusaktide t&auml;itmise kontroll </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision over implementation of legislation </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduste ja volikogu m&auml;&auml;ruste ning otsuste ja valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse m&auml;&auml;ruste ning korralduste t&auml;itmist kontrollivad seaduses ja valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras volikogu ja valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The implementation of Acts, council regulations and resolutions and rural municipality or city government regulations and orders is supervised by the council and government pursuant to the procedure provided by law and the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustus volikogu liikme ees </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation of employers to council members </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud v&otilde;imaldama volikogu liikmel osa v&otilde;tta volikogu istungitest ja tema komisjonide koosolekutest ning t&auml;ita volikogu antud &uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer is obligated to allow a council member to participate in council sessions and meetings of council committees and to perform tasks assigned to the council member by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu liikme &otilde;igus saada teavet </eesti>
<inglise>Right of council members to obtain information </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu liikmel on &otilde;igus saada volikogu ja valitsuse &otilde;igusakte, dokumente ja muud teavet, v&auml;lja arvatud andmed, mille v&auml;ljastamine on seadusega keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>Council members have the right to obtain copies of council and government legislation, documentation and other information, except for data the issue of which is prohibited by law. </inglise>
<eesti>III peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Valitsus </eesti>
<inglise>Government </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Vallavanema ja linnapea valimine </eesti>
<inglise>Election of rural municipality or city mayor </inglise>
<eesti>Vallavanema v&otilde;i linnapea valib volikogu k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud tingimustel ja korras kuni kolmeks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>A rural municipality or city mayor is elected under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act and the statutes of the rural municipality or city, for a period of up to three years. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Vallavanema ja linnapea &otilde;igus moodustada valitsus </eesti>
<inglise>Right of rural municipality or city mayor to form government </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vallavanemal v&otilde;i linnapeal on valituks osutumise p&auml;evast volitus moodustada valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A rural municipality or city mayor has the authority to form a government as of the date he or she is elected. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valitsuse moodustamise &uuml;ksikasjaline kord s&auml;testatakse valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A detailed procedure for the formation of the government shall be provided for in the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Seaduses ja valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses etten&auml;htud volitused saab vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea valitsuse ametisse kinnitamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A rural municipality or city mayor obtains the authority prescribed by law and the statutes of the rural municipality or city as of the date the appointment of the government to office is confirmed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Valitsuse volituste t&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Term of authority of government </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus saab oma volitused volikogu poolt valitsuse ametisse kinnitamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A rural municipality or city government obtains authority as of the date its appointment to office is confirmed by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valitsus esitab lahkumispalve volikogu uue koosseisu esimesel istungil. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A government shall submit its resignation at the first session of a new membership of the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) P&auml;rast lahkumispalve esitamist t&auml;idab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus oma &uuml;lesandeid ja tema volitused kehtivad kuni uue valitsuse ametisse kinnitamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) After submitting its resignation, a rural municipality or city government shall continue to perform its functions and its authority remains in force until the appointment to office of a new government is confirmed. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) (Kehtetu - 30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(4) (Repealed - 30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Valla- ja linnavalitsuse p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of rural municipality or city government </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A rural municipality or city government: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valmistab ette volikogus arutamisele tulevaid k&uuml;simusi, l&auml;htudes valitsuse seisukohtadest v&otilde;i volikogu otsustest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) prepares issues to be discussed in the council based on the position of the government or council resolutions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) lahendab ja korraldab kohaliku elu k&uuml;simusi, mis volikogu m&auml;&auml;ruste v&otilde;i otsustega v&otilde;i valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusega on pandud t&auml;itmiseks valitsusele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) resolves and manages local issues which are assigned to the government by council regulations or resolutions, or the statutes of the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>3) lahendab ja korraldab kohaliku elu k&uuml;simusi, mis ei kuulu volikogu p&auml;devusse; </eesti>
<inglise>3) resolves and manages local issues which are not within the competence of the council; </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>4) lahendab k&uuml;simusi, mis on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 22 2. l&otilde;ike alusel delegeeritud valitsusele. </eesti>
<inglise>4) resolves issues, the resolution of which has been delegated to the government on the basis of subsection 22 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valitsus v&otilde;ib taotleda volikogu ees volikogu poolt vastuv&otilde;etud m&auml;&auml;ruse v&otilde;i otsuse uuesti l&auml;bivaatamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The government may apply to the council for the review of a regulation or resolution passed by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Valla- ja linnavalitsuse m&auml;&auml;rustele ning korraldustele esitatavad n&otilde;uded ja nende j&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for rural municipality and city government regulations and orders and entry into force thereof </inglise>
<eesti>(1) M&auml;&auml;rused ja korraldused peavad olema valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses kehtestatud korras avalikustatud enne nende j&otilde;ustumist ja k&auml;ttesaadavad k&otilde;igile isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Regulations and orders shall be made public prior to the entry into force thereof and made accessible to everyone pursuant to the procedure provided for in the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ei avalikustata andmeid, mille v&auml;ljastamine on seadusega keelatud v&otilde;i m&otilde;eldud &uuml;ksnes valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuse siseseks kasutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Data the issue of which is prohibited by law or which is intended only for the internal use of rural municipality or city agencies shall not be disclosed. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valla- ja linnavalitsuse m&auml;&auml;rused ja korraldused vormistatakse ja avalikustatakse eesti keeles. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Rural municipality and city government regulations and orders are prepared and made public in Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) M&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast avalikustamist, kui m&auml;&auml;ruses eneses ei ole s&auml;testatud hilisemat t&auml;htp&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Regulations enter into force on the third day after being made public unless the regulation provides for a later date. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.01.99 j&otilde;ust.01.03.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 155) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.01.99 entered into force 01.03.99 - RT I 1999, 10, 155) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Valitsuse korraldused j&otilde;ustuvad neis etten&auml;htud t&auml;htajal ning need tuleb saata t&auml;itjatele ja teistele asjaosalistele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Government orders enter into force on the date prescribed therein and shall be forwarded to the persons who shall execute such resolutions and other persons concerned. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;rustele ja teistele valitsuse dokumentidele kirjutab alla vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea ja valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>Regulations and other government documentation shall be signed by the rural municipality or city mayor and the rural municipality or city secretary. </inglise>
<eesti>IV peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Valla- v&otilde;i linnaelanike osalemine kohaliku omavalitsuse teostamises </eesti>
<inglise>Participation of Rural Municipality or City Residents in Exercise of Local Government </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igusaktide algatamise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to initiate legislation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;hemalt &uuml;hel protsendil h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguslikel valla- v&otilde;i linnaelanikel, kuid mitte v&auml;hem kui viiel h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguslikul valla- v&otilde;i linnaelanikul, on &otilde;igus teha kohaliku elu k&uuml;simustes valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu v&otilde;i -valitsuse &otilde;igusaktide vastuv&otilde;tmiseks, muutmiseks v&otilde;i t&uuml;histamiseks algatusi, mis v&otilde;etakse arutusele hiljemalt kolme kuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Not less than one per cent of the residents of a rural municipality or city with the right to vote, however not less than five residents with the right to vote, have the right to initiate the passage, amendment or repeal of legislation of the rural municipality or city council or government concerning local issues; such initiatives shall be debated not later than within three months. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud algatus esitatakse valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele vastava eeln&otilde;una, millele lisatakse allkirjadega varustatud algatuse esitajate nimekiri. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Issues initiated pursuant to subsection (1) of this section shall be presented to the rural municipality or city government in the form of a corresponding draft to which a signed list of the initiators shall be appended. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui algatatud k&uuml;simus kuulub volikogu p&auml;devusse, esitab valitsus selle &uuml;he kuu jooksul volikogule lahendamiseks koos omapoolse seisukohaga. </eesti>
<inglise>If the initiated issue is within the competence of the council, the government shall, within one month, submit such issue together with its position to the council for resolution. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Algatuse esitajate esindajal on &otilde;igus osaleda algatuse arutelus volikogus v&otilde;i valitsuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A representative of the initiators of an issue has the right to participate in the debate of such issue in the council or the government. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudatuste taotlemine volikogu ja valitsuse &otilde;igusaktides </eesti>
<inglise>Application for amendment of council and government legislation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Iga&uuml;hel on &otilde;igus taotleda volikogult v&otilde;i valitsuselt nende poolt vastuv&otilde;etud &otilde;igusaktidesse muudatuste tegemist v&otilde;i nende t&uuml;histamist, kui nendega on seadusvastaselt kitsendatud tema &otilde;igusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Everyone has the right to apply to a rural municipality or city government for the amendment or repeal of legislation passed by the rural municipality or city government if such legislation unlawfully restricts the rights of the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui volikogu v&otilde;i valitsus j&auml;tab antud &otilde;igusakti muutmata v&otilde;i t&uuml;histamata, on taotlejal &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda k&uuml;simuse lahendamiseks kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a rural municipality or city government refuses to amend or repeal such legislation, the applicant has the right of recourse to the courts for resolution of the issue. </inglise>
<eesti>V peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Majandus ja eelarve </eesti>
<inglise>Economic Affairs and Budget </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Munitsipaalomand </eesti>
<inglise>Municipal property </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Munitsipaalomand on vallale v&otilde;i linnale kuuluv vara. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Municipal property is property in the ownership of a rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Oma vara valdamise, kasutamise ja k&auml;sutamise korra s&auml;testab valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu vastavalt seadusele valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A rural municipality or city council shall, pursuant to law, establish the procedure for possession, use and disposal of municipal property in the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kohalik omavalitsus v&otilde;ib talle riigi poolt tasuta omandisse antud kinnisasja v&otilde;&otilde;randada juhul, kui kinnisasi ei ole enam vajalik v&otilde;i on muutunud k&otilde;lbmatuks kohaliku omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A local government may transfer an immovable which has been transferred into its ownership without charge by the state if such immovable ceases to be necessary or has become unsuitable for the performance of the functions of the local government. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi poolt tasuta antud kinnisasja v&otilde;ib v&otilde;&otilde;randada ainult kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>An immovable transferred by the state without charge may be transferred only pursuant to the procedure established by the local government council. </inglise>
<eesti>(29.01.97 j&otilde;ust.02.03.97 - RT I 1997, 13, 210) </eesti>
<inglise>(29.01.97 entered into force 02.03.97 - RT I 1997, 13, 210) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kohalikul omavalitsus&uuml;ksusel on ostuees&otilde;igus tema haldusterritooriumil asuva ehitise v&otilde;&otilde;randamisel era&otilde;iguslike isikute poolt, kui seda ehitist on osaliselt v&otilde;i tervikuna enne v&otilde;&otilde;randamist v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he aasta jooksul kasutatud haridus-, tervishoiu-, kultuuri- v&otilde;i kasvatusasutusena. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A local government has the right of pre-emption upon the transfer of structures located within its administrative territory by persons in private law if such structures were, in whole or in part, used by an educational, health care, cultural or child care institution for not less than one year prior to the transfer. </inglise>
<eesti>Muus osas kohaldatakse ostuees&otilde;igusele asja&otilde;igusseaduse (RT I 1993, 39, 590; RT I 1999, 44, 509; 2001, 34, 185; 93, 565) s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>The provisions of the Law of Property Act (RT I 1993, 39, 590; RT I 1999, 44, 509; 2001, 34, 185; 93, 565) apply to the right of pre-emption otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti>(29.01.97 j&otilde;ust.02.03.97 - RT I 1997, 13, 210) </eesti>
<inglise>(29.01.97 entered into force 02.03.97 - RT I 1997, 13, 210) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Majandustegevus ja osalemine juriidilistes isikutes </eesti>
<inglise>Economic activities and participation in legal persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vald v&otilde;i linn v&otilde;ib teenuste osutamiseks asutada valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuse hallatavaid asutusi, mis ei ole juriidilised isikud, olla osanikuks v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;riks valla v&otilde;i linna arengu seisukohast olulises &auml;ri&uuml;hingus, samuti asutada sihtasutusi ja olla mittetulundus&uuml;hingu liikmeks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A rural municipality or city may found agencies under the administration of rural municipality or city administrative agencies which are not legal persons for the provision of services, may be a partner or shareholder in a company of significant importance in the development of the rural municipality or city, may found foundations and be a member of a non-profit association. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuse hallatava asutuse asutamise ja selle tegevuse l&otilde;petamise otsustab volikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The local government council shall decide on the foundation and termination of the activities of agencies under the administration of rural municipality or city administrative agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>Hallatava asutuse p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse kinnitamine ja selle muutmine toimub volikogu poolt s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The statutes of the agencies under the administration of rural municipality or city administrative agencies shall be approved and amended pursuant to the procedure provided for by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>Valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutus ja ametiasutuse hallatav asutus registreeritakse riigi ja kohaliku omavalitsuse asutuste registris. </eesti>
<inglise>Rural municipality and city administrative agencies and agencies under the administration of rural municipality or city administrative agencies shall be registered in the register of state and local government agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Sihtasutuse, mille ainuasutajaks on vald v&otilde;i linn, samuti osa&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i aktsiaseltsi, mille ainsaks osanikuks v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;riks on vald v&otilde;i linn, asutamise, &uuml;hinemise, jagunemise ja &uuml;mberkujundamise ja l&otilde;petamise otsustab ning p&otilde;hikirja ja selle muudatused kinnitab kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The local government council shall decide on the foundation, merger, division and transformation and termination of foundations of which the rural municipality or city is the sole founder, and of private limited companies and public limited companies of which the rural municipality or city is the sole partner or shareholder, and approve the statutes of such foundations, private limited companies and public limited companies and amendments thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>Sihtasutuse, osa&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i aktsiaseltsi n&otilde;ukogu liikmed nimetab, samuti muid asutaja, osaniku v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;ri &otilde;igusi teostab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The rural municipality or city government shall appoint the members of the supervisory boards of such foundations, private limited companies or public limited companies and exercise the other rights of a founder, partner or shareholder. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui osa&uuml;hingul ei ole n&otilde;ukogu, nimetab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus osa&uuml;hingu juhatuse liikmed. </eesti>
<inglise>If a private limited company does not have a supervisory board, the rural municipality or city government shall nominate the members of its management board. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.19.07.96 - RT I 1996, 48, 942; 17.06.98 j&otilde;ust 10.07.98 - RT I 1998, 59, 941) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 19.07.96 - RT I 1996, 48, 942; 17.06.98 entered into force 10.07.98 - RT I 1998, 59, 941) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui sihtasutusel on mitu asutajat v&otilde;i kui &auml;ri&uuml;hingus osaleb lisaks linnale v&otilde;i vallale ka teisi osanikke v&otilde;i aktsion&auml;re, samuti kui vald v&otilde;i linn osaleb liikmena mittetulundus&uuml;hingus, otsustab osalemise ja selle l&otilde;petamise valla- v&otilde;i linnavolikogu. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a foundation has several founders or if other partners or shareholders in addition to a city or rural municipality participate in a company, or if a rural municipality or city is a member of a non-profit association, participation in and termination thereof shall be decided by the rural municipality or city council. </inglise>
<eesti>Muus osas teostab osaniku-, aktsion&auml;ri-, asutaja- v&otilde;i liikme&otilde;igusi valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse poolt nimetatud isik. </eesti>
<inglise>Otherwise the rights of a partner, shareholder, founder or member are exercised by persons appointed by the rural municipality or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.19.07.96 - RT I 1996, 48, 942) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 19.07.96 - RT I 1996, 48, 942) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Vallal v&otilde;i linnal on &otilde;igus oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks s&otilde;lmida lepinguid. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Rural municipalities and cities have the right to enter into contracts for the performance of their functions. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingute s&otilde;lmimiseks volitatud isikud m&auml;&auml;ratakse valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The persons authorised to enter into contracts shall be appointed by the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksud ja koormised </eesti>
<inglise>Taxes and duties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohalikud maksud ja maksum&auml;&auml;rade muudatused kehtestatakse enne valla- v&otilde;i linnaeelarve v&otilde;i lisaeelarve vastuv&otilde;tmist v&otilde;i eelarve muutmist ja neid rakendatakse eelarveaasta algusest v&otilde;i koos lisaeelarve v&otilde;i eelarve muutmisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Local taxes and amendments to tax rates shall be established prior to the passage or amendment of a rural municipality or city budget or supplementary budget and shall be implemented from the beginning of the budgetary year or together with the amendments to the supplementary budget or budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koormis on kohustus, mis seaduse alusel kehtestatakse volikogu m&auml;&auml;rusega f&uuml;&uuml;silistele v&otilde;i juriidilistele isikutele kohustuslike t&ouml;&ouml;de tegemiseks valla v&otilde;i linna territooriumil kehtestatud heakorraeeskirjade t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A duty is an obligation which is imposed on natural or legal persons pursuant to law by a council regulation for the performance of mandatory work for the fulfilment of the property maintenance rules established on the territory of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Koormise v&otilde;ib kehtestada f&uuml;&uuml;silistele ja juriidilistele isikutele nende omandis v&otilde;i valduses oleva kinnistu v&otilde;i muu nende kasutuses oleva territooriumi ning sellega vahetult piirneva &uuml;ldkasutatava territooriumi heakorra tagamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Duties may be imposed on a natural or legal person pursuant to law to ensure compliance with the property maintenance rules on the territory of immovables in their ownership or possession, or any other territory in their use, and on public lands directly bordering such territories. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Koormise m&auml;&auml;ramisel kehtestatakse koormise olemus, ulatus, t&auml;itmise tingimused ja kord. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The nature, scope, terms and procedure for the fulfilment of duties shall be specified upon the imposition thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Isik, kellel koormise t&auml;itmine lasub, v&otilde;ib oma arvel lasta selle t&auml;ita teisel isikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A person with whom the fulfilment of a duty rests, may have another person fulfil such duty at his or her expense. </inglise>
<eesti>Isiku p&otilde;hjendatud taotlusel on volikogul &otilde;igus lubada isikul koormise t&auml;itmise eest maksta raha, mida peab kasutama selle koormise t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon a reasoned request of a person, a council has the right to allow the person to pay for the fulfilment of duties in money, which shall be used for the fulfilment of such duties. </inglise>
<eesti>Koormise t&auml;itmiseks vajalike t&ouml;&ouml;de maksumus m&auml;&auml;ratakse koormise kehtestamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>The cost of work necessary for the fulfilment of duties shall be specified upon the imposition of such duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Koormise t&auml;itmist kontrollib valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus vastavalt valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses kehtestatud korrale. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The fulfilment of duties shall be supervised by the rural municipality or city government pursuant to the procedure established by the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Koormist ei v&otilde;i asendada maksuga kohalikku eelarvesse. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Duties shall not be substituted by taxes which accrue to the local budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Koormisena ei v&otilde;i kehtestada trahve, teenustasusid, l&otilde;ive ega muu nimetusega rahalisi makseid. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Fines, service charges, fees or monetary payments by any other name shall not be imposed as duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Koormis ei v&otilde;i olla lepingu objektiks. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Duties shall not be the object of a contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.02.95 j&otilde;ust.10.03.95 - RT I 1995, 17, 237) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.02.95 entered into force 10.03.95 - RT I 1995, 17, 237) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Arengukava vastuv&otilde;tmine ja muutmine </eesti>
<inglise>Passage and amendment of development plans </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vallal v&otilde;i linnal peab olema arengukava v&auml;hemalt kolmeks j&auml;rgnevaks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A rural municipality or city shall have a development plan for not less than three subsequent years. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui vallal v&otilde;i linnal on kolmest aastast pikemaajalisi varalisi kohustusi v&otilde;i neid kavandatakse pikemaks perioodiks, peab arengukava olema kavandatud selleks perioodiks. </eesti>
<inglise>If a rural municipality or city has financial obligations for a period longer than three years or financial obligations are planned for a longer period, the development plan shall be prepared for such period. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arengukava ja selle muutmise eeln&otilde;u avalikustatakse enne selle vastuv&otilde;tmist volikogus valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Development plans and draft resolutions for the amendment of development plans are made public pursuant to the procedure provided for in the statutes of the rural municipality or city prior to the passage thereof by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Hiljemalt iga aasta 1. oktoobriks vaatab volikogu l&auml;bi ja v&otilde;tab vastu otsuse arengukava muutmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Not later than by 1 October each year, the council shall review and pass a resolution on the amendment of the development plan. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arengukava on aluseks: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The development plan is the basis for: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valla- v&otilde;i linnaeelarve koostamisele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the preparation of a rural municipality or city budget; </inglise>
<eesti>2) investeeringute kavandamisele ja nende jaoks rahaliste ja muude vahendite taotlemisele, s&otilde;ltumata nende allikast; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the planning of investments, and the application for funds and other means for such investments regardless of the source; </inglise>
<eesti>3) laenude v&otilde;tmisele ja v&otilde;lakirjade emiteerimisele eelarveaastast pikemaks perioodiks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the taking of loans and the issue of debt instruments for a period longer than a budgetary year. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Valla v&otilde;i linna &uuml;ldplaneering ja arengukava ei tohi olla vastuolus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The general plan and development plan of a rural municipality or city shall not be in conflict. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Valla ja linna eelarve </eesti>
<inglise>Rural municipality and city budgets </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Valla v&otilde;i linna iseseisev eelarve koosneb &uuml;he eelarveaasta tuludest ja kuludest, mis kokkuv&otilde;ttes viiakse tasakaalu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The independent budget of a rural municipality or city is composed of all the revenue and expenditure for one budgetary year, which are balanced. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vallal v&otilde;i linnal on keelatud laenu andmine v&otilde;i tagamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Rural municipalities and cities shall not grant or secure loans. </inglise>
<eesti>Laenu v&otilde;ib anda &uuml;ksnes &otilde;ppelaenuks linna- v&otilde;i vallaeelarves selleks otstarbeks etten&auml;htud summa piirides. </eesti>
<inglise>Only student loans may be granted within the amount prescribed for such purpose in the rural municipality or city budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(11.10.94 j&otilde;ust.10.11.94 - RT I 1994, 72, 1263) </eesti>
<inglise>(11.10.94 entered into force 10.11.94 - RT I 1994, 72, 1263) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eelarve projekt, vastuv&otilde;etud eelarve ning eelarve muudatused ja eelarve t&auml;itmise aruanne avaldatakse &uuml;ldiseks teadmiseks valla- v&otilde;i linnaelanikele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Draft budgets, passed budgets, amendments thereto and reports on the implementation thereof shall be published as public information for the residents of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) (Kehtetu - 09.02.95 j&otilde;ust.10.03.95 - RT I 1995, 17, 237) </eesti>
<inglise>(4) (Repealed - 09.02.95 entered into force 10.03.95 - RT I 1995, 17, 237) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Valla ja linna eelarve koostamine ja j&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise>Draft of and entry into force of rural municipality and city budgets </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Valla v&otilde;i linna eelarve koostatakse seaduses s&auml;testatud korras, arvestades valla v&otilde;i linna arengukava. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Rural municipality and city budgets are drafted pursuant to the procedure provided by law, taking into consideration the development plan of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eelarve v&otilde;i selle projekti muutmise ettepanekule, mis tingib nendes etten&auml;htud tulude v&auml;hendamise, kulude suurendamise v&otilde;i kulude &uuml;mberjaotamise, tuleb algatajal lisada rahalised arvestused, mis n&auml;itavad &auml;ra kulude katteks vajalikud tuluallikad. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Initiators of amendments to a budget or draft budget which bring about a decrease in revenue, or an increase or reallocation of expenditure, shall append calculations indicating the sources of revenue necessary to cover such expenditure. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valla v&otilde;i linna eelarve j&otilde;ustub seaduses etten&auml;htud t&auml;htajast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Rural municipality and city budgets enter into force on the date prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39.1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39.1. </inglise>
<eesti>Eelarve t&auml;itmise aruande kinnitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Report on the implementation of rural municipality and city budgets </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogule kinnitamiseks esitatavale eelarve t&auml;itmise aruandele peab olema lisatud volikogu poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud audiitori arvamus aruande kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The opinion of an auditor appointed by the council concerning the report on the implementation of the rural municipality or city budget shall be appended to the report submitted for approval to the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eelarve t&auml;itmise aruande kinnitab volikogu hiljemalt 1. juuniks, olles eelnevalt &auml;ra kuulanud revisjonikomisjoni vastava arvamuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The council shall approve the report on the implementation of the rural municipality or city budget not later than by 1 June after having heard the opinion of the audit committee on the report. </inglise>
<eesti>Eelarve t&auml;itmise aruanne avalikustatakse valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The report on the implementation of a rural municipality or city budget shall be made public pursuant to the procedure provided for in the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>VI peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Administration </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;vormid </eesti>
<inglise>Work format </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu ja valitsuse t&ouml;&ouml; vorm on istung. </eesti>
<inglise>Councils and governments conduct work in sessions. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu ja valitsuse komisjoni t&ouml;&ouml; vorm on koosolek. </eesti>
<inglise>Council and government committees conduct work in meetings. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Keelekasutus kohalikes omavalitsustes </eesti>
<inglise>Use of language in local governments </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Asjaajamiskeel kohalikes omavalitsustes on eesti keel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The working language of local governments is Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>Iga&uuml;hel on &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda kohalike omavalitsuste ja nende ametiisikute poole eesti keeles ja saada eestikeelseid vastuseid. </eesti>
<inglise>Everyone has the right to address a local government and its officials in Estonian and to receive responses in Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogu ja valitsuse istungid toimuvad eesti keeles. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The sessions of councils and governments are held in Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&otilde;&otilde;rkeelte, sealhulgas v&auml;hemusrahvuste keelte kasutamise kohalikes omavalitsustes s&auml;testab keeleseadus (RT I 1995, 23, 334; 1996, 37, 739; 40, 773; 1997, 69, 1110; 1998, 98/99, 1618; 1999, 1, 1; 16, 275; 2000, 51, 326; 2001, 58, 354; 65, 375; 93, 565). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The use of foreign languages in local governments, including languages of national minorities shall be provided for in the Language Act (RT I 1995, 23, 334; 1996, 37, 739; 40, 773; 1997, 69, 1110; 1998, 98/99, 1618; 1999, 1, 1; 16, 275; 60, 618; 2000, 51, 326; 2001, 58, 354; 65, 375; 93, 565). </inglise>
<eesti>Keeleseaduse &sect; 11 alusel kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu ettepanekul antud luba kasutada vastava kohaliku omavalitsuse sisemise asjaajamise keelena omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse p&uuml;sielanike enamiku moodustava v&auml;hemusrahvuse keelt kehtib kuni vastava volikogu volituste l&otilde;ppemiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>The permission granted on the proposal of the corresponding local government council pursuant to &sect; 11 of the Language Act to use the language of the national minority constituting the majority of the permanent residents of the local government alongside Estonian as the internal working language of the local government shall be valid until the authority of the corresponding council terminates. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui omavalitsus&uuml;ksus on vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikele saanud n&otilde;usoleku kasutada sisemise asjaajamise keelena eesti keele k&otilde;rval omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse p&uuml;sielanike enamiku moodustava v&auml;hemusrahvuse keelt, v&otilde;ivad volikogu ja valitsus otsustada vastavalt volikogu ja valitsuse istungi t&ouml;&ouml; osalise v&otilde;i t&auml;ieliku t&otilde;lkimise v&auml;hemusrahvuse keelde. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a local government has been granted, pursuant to subsection (3) of this section, the permission to use the language of the national minority constituting the majority of the permanent residents of the local government alongside Estonian as the internal working language of the local government, the council and the government may decide to translate part or whole of the sessions into the language of the national minority. </inglise>
<eesti>(04.12.2001 j&otilde;ust.21.10.2002 - RT I 2001, 100, 642) </eesti>
<inglise>(04.12.2001 entered into force 21.10.2002 - RT I 2001, 100, 642) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu esimees </eesti>
<inglise>Chairman of council </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu esimees: </eesti>
<inglise>The chairman of a council: </inglise>
<eesti>1) korraldab volikogu t&ouml;&ouml;d, kutsub kokku ja juhatab volikogu istungeid ning korraldab nende ettevalmistamist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) manages the work of the council, convenes and chairs the sessions of the council and organises the preparation thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>2) esindab omavalitsus&uuml;ksust ja selle volikogu vastavalt seadusega, valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusega ning volikogu poolt antud p&auml;devusele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) represents the local government and its council in accordance with the competence granted by law, the statutes of the rural municipality or city and the council; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kirjutab alla volikogu poolt vastuv&otilde;etud m&auml;&auml;rustele ja teistele volikogu dokumentidele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) signs regulations passed by the council and other council documentation; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&auml;idab muid talle seaduse alusel ja valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusega pandud &uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>4) performs other functions assigned to him or her pursuant to law and the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu kokkukutsumine </eesti>
<inglise>Convention of council sessions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu istungi kutsub kokku selle esimees v&otilde;i tema asendaja, nende puudumisel volikogu vanim liige volikogu poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Council sessions are convened by the chairman or the deputy chairman or, in the absence thereof, by the eldest member of the council pursuant to the procedure established by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu esimese istungi kutsub kokku valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjoni esimees hiljemalt seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast valimistulemuste v&auml;ljakuulutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>The first council session is convened by the chairman of the rural municipality or city election committee not later than on the seventh day after the declaration of the election results. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu esimese istungi ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 52 2. l&otilde;ike alusel kokkukutsutava istungi kutse saatmisel ei ole vaja j&auml;rgida k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>Compliance with the requirements prescribed in subsection (3) of this section is not necessary upon the sending of invitations to the first council session and to a council session to be convened pursuant to subsection 52 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kehtetu - 16.05.96 j&otilde;ust.08.06.96 - RT I 1996, 37, 739) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 16.05.96 entered into force 08.06.96 - RT I 1996, 37, 739) </inglise>
<eesti>(2 (1)) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 52 2. l&otilde;ike alusel kokkukutsutava volikogu istungi kutsub kokku valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjoni esimees hiljemalt seitsmendal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast asendusliikmete m&auml;&auml;ramist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2 (1)) The council session to be convened pursuant to subsection 52 (2) of this Act is convened by the chairman of the rural municipality or city election committee not later than on the seventh day after the designation of an alternate council member. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Volikogu kokkukutsumisel tuleb kutses &auml;ra n&auml;idata arutusele tulevad k&uuml;simused ja kutse peab olema volikogu liikmetele teatavaks tehtud v&auml;hemalt neli p&auml;eva enne volikogu istungit. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon convention of a council session, issues to be discussed shall be indicated in the notice of the session which shall be forwarded to the council members not less than four days prior to the council session. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Volikogu esimees v&otilde;i tema asendaja kutsub volikogu kokku valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse v&otilde;i v&auml;hemalt neljandiku volikogu koosseisu ettepanekul nende poolt t&otilde;statatud k&uuml;simuste arutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The chairman or deputy chairman of a council shall convene a council session on the proposal of the rural municipality or city government or of not less than one fourth of the membership of the council for the discussion of issues raised by them. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>K&uuml;simuste arutelu volikogus </eesti>
<inglise>Discussion of issues by council </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu t&ouml;&ouml;d korraldab ja istungeid juhatab volikogu esimees v&otilde;i tema asendaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The work of a council is organised and sessions are chaired by the chairman or deputy chairman of the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogu esimees korraldab vajadusel arutusele tulevate k&uuml;simuste ettevalmistamist volikogu poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The chairman of the council shall organise, where necessary, the preparation by the council of issues to be discussed. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu v&otilde;ib valitsusele anda ettevalmistamiseks volikogus arutusele tulevaid k&uuml;simusi. </eesti>
<inglise>The council may assign the preparation of issues to be discussed in the council to the government. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Volikogu esimest istungit juhatab kuni volikogu esimehe valimiseni valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjoni esimees. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The first council session shall be chaired by the chairman of the rural municipality or city election committee until the chairman of the council is elected. </inglise>
<eesti>Esimese istungi p&auml;evakorras on volikogu esimehe ja aseesimehe v&otilde;i aseesimeeste valimine ning valitsuse lahkumispalve &auml;rakuulamine. </eesti>
<inglise>The agenda of the first session shall include the election of the chairman and deputy chairman or deputy chairmen of the council, and consideration of the resignation of the government. </inglise>
<eesti>Sama kord kehtib ka k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 52 2. l&otilde;ike alusel kokkukutsutud uue volikogu esimese istungi p&auml;evakorra suhtes, v&auml;lja arvatud valitsuse lahkumispalve &auml;rakuulamine. </eesti>
<inglise>The same procedure also applies to the agenda of the first session of a new council convened pursuant to subsection 52 (2) of this Act, except for the consideration of the resignation of the government. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu esimehe ja aseesimehe valimised korraldab valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjon ning valimistulemused tehakse kindlaks valimiskomisjoni otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The election of the chairman and deputy chairman of the council shall be organised by the rural municipality or city election committee and the election results shall be established by a resolution of the election committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Volikogu istungid on avalikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Council sessions are public. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu v&otilde;ib kuulutada istungi k&uuml;simuse arutelu osas kinniseks, kui selle poolt h&auml;&auml;letab v&auml;hemalt kaks korda enam volikogu liikmeid kui vastu v&otilde;i kui k&uuml;simust puudutavate andmete avalikustamine on seadusega keelatud v&otilde;i piiratud. </eesti>
<inglise>A council may declare a session to be closed in the part of the discussion of an issue if at least twice as many members of the council vote in favour of such proposal as against it, or if the disclosure of data pertaining to the issue under discussion is prohibited or restricted by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Volikogu arutab istungi kutses m&auml;rgitud ja volikogu poolt n&otilde;utavas korras ettevalmistatud k&uuml;simusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A council discusses issues indicated in the notice of the session and prepared pursuant to the procedure required by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Volikogu istungist v&otilde;ivad s&otilde;na&otilde;igusega osa v&otilde;tta valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse liikmed, valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r, samuti volikogu poolt istungile kutsutud isikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The members of the rural municipality or city government, the rural municipality or city secretary and persons invited to a session by the council may participate in the session of the council with the right to speak. </inglise>
<eesti>S&otilde;na andmise otsustab istungi juhataja. </eesti>
<inglise>The chair of the session decides on whether to assign the floor to such persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>H&auml;&auml;letamine volikogus </eesti>
<inglise>Voting in council </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu ainup&auml;devusse kuuluvaid k&uuml;simusi otsustatakse h&auml;&auml;letamise teel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Issues which are within the exclusive competence of a council are decided by a vote. </inglise>
<eesti>Muudes k&uuml;simustes h&auml;&auml;letatakse juhul, kui v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks volikogu liige seda n&otilde;uab. </eesti>
<inglise>Other issues shall be decided by a vote upon the request of at least one council member. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) H&auml;&auml;letamine volikogus on avalik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Voting in councils is open. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Isikuvalimised otsustatakse salajasel h&auml;&auml;letamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The election of persons shall be decided by secret ballot. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.06.98 j&otilde;ust.16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 61, 984) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.06.98 entered into force 16.07.98 - RT I 1998, 61, 984) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Volikogu otsustused fikseerib istungi juhataja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Council decisions shall be documented by the chair of the session. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Volikogu otsustused tehakse poolth&auml;&auml;lte enamusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Council decisions shall be passed by a majority of votes in favour. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 22 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 2, 4, 6-10, 14, 15, 18 ja 24 etten&auml;htud k&uuml;simustes otsustuste vastuv&otilde;tmiseks on vajalik volikogu koosseisu h&auml;&auml;lteenamus. </eesti>
<inglise>A majority of votes of the membership of the council is required to adopt the decisions specified in clauses 22 (1) 2), 4), 6) -10), 14), 15), 18) and 24) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>Umbusaldusmenetlus volikogus </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for expression of no confidence in council </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;hemalt neljandik volikogu koosseisust v&otilde;ib algatada umbusalduse avaldamise volikogu esimehele, volikogu aseesimehele, volikogu komisjoni esimehele, volikogu komisjoni aseesimehele, revisjonikomisjoni liikmele, valitsusele, vallavanemale, linnapeale v&otilde;i valitsuse liikmele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Not less than one fourth of the members of a council may initiate an expression of no confidence in the chairman of the council, deputy chairman of the council, chairman of a council committee, deputy chairman of a council committee, a member of the audit committee, the government, the rural municipality or city mayor or a member of the government. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Umbusalduse avaldamise k&uuml;simus l&uuml;litatakse volikogu j&auml;rgmise istungi p&auml;evakorda. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The issue of expression of no confidence shall be included in the agenda of the next council session. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Umbusaldush&auml;&auml;letus on avalik. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The vote of no confidence is public. </inglise>
<eesti>Umbusalduse avaldamine vabastab volikogu esimehe v&otilde;i aseesimehe tema kohustustest ja ametist v&otilde;i volikogu komisjoni esimehe, komisjoni aseesimehe v&otilde;i revisjonikomisjoni liikme tema kohustustest. </eesti>
<inglise>Expression of no confidence releases the chairman or deputy chairman of the council from his or her duties and office, and the chairman or deputy chairman of a council committee, or a member of the audit committee from his or her duties. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu esimehele umbusalduse avaldamise korral t&auml;idab volikogu esimehe &uuml;lesandeid kuni uue esimehe valimiseni volikogu m&auml;&auml;ratud &uuml;ks volikogu aseesimeestest v&otilde;i tema puudumisel volikogu vanim liige. </eesti>
<inglise>In the event of an expression of no confidence in the chairman of a council, the duties of the chairman of the council shall be performed by one deputy chairman of the council appointed by the council, or in the absence thereof, the eldest member of the council, until the election of a new chairman. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Umbusalduse avaldamine vabastab vallavanema, linnapea v&otilde;i valitsuse liikme vallavanema, linnapea v&otilde;i valitsuse liikme kohustustest ja ametist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Expression of no confidence releases a rural municipality or city mayor or a member of the government from the duties and office of rural municipality or city mayor or member of the government. </inglise>
<eesti>Vallavanemale v&otilde;i linnapeale umbusalduse avaldamise korral valib volikogu samal istungil uue vallavanema v&otilde;i linnapea v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;rab &uuml;he valitsuse liikmetest vallavanema v&otilde;i linnapea asendajaks kuni uue vallavanema v&otilde;i linnapea valimiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>In the event of expression of no confidence in rural municipality or city mayor, the council shall elect a new rural municipality or city mayor at the same council session, or appoint one of the members of the government to act as substitute for the rural municipality or city mayor, until the election of a new rural municipality or city mayor. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Valitsusele umbusalduse avaldamise korral t&auml;idab valitsus oma &uuml;lesandeid edasi ja valitsuse volitused kehtivad kuni uuele valitsusele volituste andmiseni k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the event of expression of no confidence in the government, the government shall continue to perform its duties and the authority of the government shall not terminate until the new government is granted authority pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Valitsuse volituste l&otilde;ppemine seoses umbusalduse avaldamisega toob kaasa k&otilde;igi valitsuse liikmete vabastamise valitsuse liikme kohustustest ning palgaliste valitsuse liikmete ametist vabastamise. </eesti>
<inglise>The termination of the authority of the government related to the expression of no confidence shall result in the release of all the members of the government from the duties of a member of government, and the release from office of all the members of the government working in remunerative positions. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui volikogu avaldab umbusaldust m&otilde;nele valitsuse liikmele ning k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 49 6. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud kvoorum j&auml;&auml;b alles, j&auml;tkab valitsus oma tegevust ning vabad kohad t&auml;idetakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 28 s&auml;testatud korras v&otilde;i muudetakse s&auml;testatud korras valitsuse liikmete arvu ja valitsuse struktuuri. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If the council expresses no confidence in some of the government members and the quorum provided for in subsection 49 (6) of this Act is preserved, the government shall continue to act and the vacant positions shall be filled pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 28 of this Act, or the number of government members and the structure of the government is changed pursuant to the established procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui valitsuse liikmetele avaldatud umbusalduse tagaj&auml;rjel ei ole t&auml;idetud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 49 6. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud kvoorumin&otilde;ue, loetakse valitsus tervikuna tagasiastunuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If the requirement for quorum provided for in subsection 49 (6) of this Act cannot be complied with due to the expression of no confidence in government members, the entire government is deemed to be retired. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Kui umbusalduse avaldamine ei leidnud volikogu istungil toetust, siis ei saa samale isikule kolme kuu jooksul samal p&otilde;hjusel algatada uut umbusalduse avaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) If an expression of no confidence finds no support in a council session, an expression of no confidence in the same person shall not be initiated for the same reason within three months. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Umbusalduse avaldamine on volikogu esimehe, aseesimehe, vallavanema, linnapea v&otilde;i valitsuse liikme ametist vabastamise eraldi alus avaliku teenistuse seaduses (RT I 1995, 16, 228; RT I 1999, 7, 112; 10, 155; 16, 271 ja 276; 2000, 25, 144 ja 145; 28, 167; 102, 672; 2001, 7, 17 ja 18; 17, 78; 42, 233; 47, 260) s&auml;testatud ametist vabastamise aluste k&otilde;rval. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) In addition to the grounds for release from office provided in the Public Service Act (RT I 1995, 16, 228; RT I 1999, 7, 112; 10, 155; 16, 271 and 276; 2000, 25, 144 and 145; 28, 167; 102, 672; 2001, 7, 17 and 18; 17, 78; 42, 233; 47, 260), expression of no confidence is considered as separate grounds for the release from office of a chairman or deputy chairman of the council, rural municipality or city mayor or a member of the government. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu komisjonid </eesti>
<inglise>Council committees </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu v&otilde;ib moodustada nii alatisi kui ka ajutisi komisjone. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Councils may form standing committees and ad hoc committees. </inglise>
<eesti>Komisjonide esimehed tuleb valida volikogu liikmete hulgast. </eesti>
<inglise>Chairmen of committees shall be elected from among the members of the council. </inglise>
<eesti>Teised komisjoni liikmed kinnitatakse komisjoni esimehe esildusel. </eesti>
<inglise>The appointment of other committee members is confirmed on the proposal of the chairman of the committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Volikogu komisjoni tegevuse alused ja kord s&auml;testatakse valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The bases and procedure for the activities of council committees shall be provided by the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>Revisjonikomisjon </eesti>
<inglise>Audit committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu moodustab oma volituste ajaks v&auml;hemalt kolmeliikmelise revisjonikomisjoni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A council shall form an audit committee of not less than three members for the duration of its term of office. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Revisjonikomisjoni esimees ja liikmed valitakse volikogu liikmete hulgast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The chairman and members of an audit committee shall be elected from among the council members. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Revisjonikomisjon kontrollib: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The audit committee shall monitor: </inglise>
<eesti>1) valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse tegevuse vastavust volikogu m&auml;&auml;rustele ja otsustele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the conformity of the activities of the rural municipality or city government with the regulations and resolutions of the council; </inglise>
<eesti>2) valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuste ja nende hallatavate asutuste raamatupidamise &otilde;igsust ja valla v&otilde;i linna vara kasutamise sihip&auml;rasust; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the accuracy of accounting of rural municipality or city administrative agencies and agencies under the administration of a rural municipality or city administrative agencies, and the purposeful use of rural municipality or city funds; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tulude t&auml;htaegset sissen&otilde;udmist ja arvelev&otilde;tmist ning kulude vastavust valla v&otilde;i linna eelarvele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the timely collection and registration of revenue and the conformity of expenditure with the rural municipality or city budget; </inglise>
<eesti>4) valla v&otilde;i linna poolt s&otilde;lmitud lepingute t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the performance of contracts entered into by the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>5) valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse ja nende ametiasutuste tegevuse seaduslikkust ning otstarbekust. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the lawfulness and purposefulness of the activities of the rural municipality or city government and the agencies thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Revisjonikomisjon kontrollib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud asutusi valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras ja oma t&ouml;&ouml;plaani alusel v&otilde;i volikogu &uuml;lesandel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The audit committee shall monitor the agencies specified in subsection (3) of this section pursuant to the procedure provided by the statutes of the rural municipality or city and on the basis of its work schedule, or as required by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Revisjonikomisjoni otsus ja revisjoniakt saadetakse valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele, kes v&otilde;tab revisjoniakti suhtes seisukoha ja esitab selle k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul revisjonikomisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The decision of the audit committee and audit report shall be sent to the rural municipality or city government which shall take a position concerning the audit report and present it to the audit committee within ten days. </inglise>
<eesti>Revisjonikomisjon esitab eelnimetatud dokumendid volikogule otsuse tegemiseks kontrolli tulemuste realiseerimise kohta, lisades nendele dokumentidele otsuse tegemiseks vajaliku volikogu &otilde;igusakti eeln&otilde;u. </eesti>
<inglise>To enable the passing of a resolution concerning application of the results of the audit, the audit committee shall submit the documents specified above to the council, and annex the draft legislation of the council necessary to make the decision to the documents. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Revisjonikomisjonil on &otilde;igus saada teavet ja k&otilde;iki oma t&ouml;&ouml;ks vajalikke dokumente. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An audit committee has the right to obtain all information and documentation necessary for the performance of its work. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Revisjonikomisjon esitab v&auml;hemalt kord aastas aruande oma tegevuse kohta volikogu istungil. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The audit committee shall present a report concerning its activities at least once a year at a council session. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>Valitsuse t&ouml;&ouml; korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of government work </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vallavalitsuse juht on vallavanem ning linnavalitsuse juht linnapea, kes esindab valitsust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The head of a rural municipality government is the rural municipality mayor and the head of a city government is the city mayor, who represent the government. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea annab valitsuse ja valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuste sisemise t&ouml;&ouml; korraldamiseks k&auml;skkirju. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Rural municipality and city mayors issue directives for the organisation of the internal operations of the government and rural municipality or city agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valitsuse juht ei v&otilde;i olla volikogu esimees. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The chairman of a council shall not head the government. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valitsuse koosseisu kuuluvad vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea, valitsuse liikmed. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The rural municipality or city mayor and members of the government belong to the membership of the government. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Vallavanema v&otilde;i linnapea asendamine toimub valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A rural municipality or city mayor is substituted for pursuant to the procedure provided for in the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus on otsustusv&otilde;imeline, kui tema istungist v&otilde;tab peale vallavanema v&otilde;i linnapea v&otilde;i nende asendaja osa v&auml;hemalt pool valitsuse kooseisust. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A rural municipality or city government has a quorum if, in addition to the rural municipality or city mayor or his or her deputy, at least one half of the membership of the government participates in the session. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Valitsuse otsustused tehakse poolth&auml;&auml;lte enamusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Government decisions are passed by a majority of votes in favour. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Valitsuse istungid on kinnised, kui valitsus ei otsusta teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Government sessions are closed unless the government decides otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea v&otilde;i nende asendaja v&otilde;ib istungile kutsuda ka teisi isikuid. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) A rural municipality or city mayor or his or her deputy may invite other persons to participate in a session. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusele ja teistele dokumentidele kirjutavad alla vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea v&otilde;i nende asendaja ning valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) Rural municipality or city government regulations and other documentation shall be signed by the rural municipality or city mayor or his or her deputy, and the rural municipality or city secretary. </inglise>
<eesti>(11) Valla- ja linnavalitsuse t&auml;psem t&ouml;&ouml;kord, komisjonide moodustamise alused ja kord ning tegevuse alused s&auml;testatakse valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(11) The specific work procedures for a rural municipality or city government, the bases and procedure for the formation of committees and the bases for their activities shall be provided for in the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>Vallavanem ja linnapea </eesti>
<inglise>Rural municipality and city mayors </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A rural municipality or city mayor: </inglise>
<eesti>1) korraldab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse t&ouml;&ouml;d ja valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse istungite ettevalmistamist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) organises the work of the rural municipality or city government and preparation for the sessions of the rural municipality or city government; </inglise>
<eesti>2) esindab omavalitsus&uuml;ksust ja valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsust vastavalt seadusega, valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusega ning volikogu poolt antud p&auml;devusele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) represents the local government and rural municipality or city government in accordance with the competence granted by law, the statutes of the rural municipality or city and the council; </inglise>
<eesti>3) annab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse ja tema ametiasutuste sisemise t&ouml;&ouml; korraldamiseks k&auml;skkirju; </eesti>
<inglise>3) issues directives for the organisation of the internal operations of the rural municipality or city government and its agencies; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kirjutab alla valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse m&auml;&auml;rustele ja korraldustele ning teistele valitsuse dokumentidele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) signs rural municipality or city regulations and orders, and other government documentation; </inglise>
<eesti>5) esitab volikogule kinnitamiseks valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse koosseisu; </eesti>
<inglise>5) submits the membership of the rural municipality or city government to the council for confirmation; </inglise>
<eesti>6) esitab volikogule ettepaneku valitsuse t&auml;iendava liikme kinnitamiseks ja valitsuse liikme vabastamiseks valitsuse liikme kohustustest ning palgalise valitsuse liikme ametisse nimetamiseks ja ametist vabastamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>6) submits a proposal to the council for the confirmation of the appointment to office and release from the duties of a member of government of the additional members of the rural municipality or city government, and the appointment to and release from remunerative positions of members of the government; </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>7) esitab valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsusele ametisse kinnitamiseks ametiasutuse hallatava asutuse juhi kandidaadi; </eesti>
<inglise>7) presents candidates for the heads of agencies under the administration of rural municipality or city administrative agencies to the city or rural municipality government for confirmation of the appointment to office; </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>7 (1)) esitab majanduslike huvide deklaratsiooni korruptsioonivastases seaduses s&auml;testatud korras; </eesti>
<inglise>7 (1)) submits a declaration of economic interests pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Anti-corruption Act; </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>8) t&auml;idab muid talle seaduse alusel ja valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rusega pandud &uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>8) performs other functions assigned to him or her pursuant to law and the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea ei tohi olla &uuml;heski muus riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse ametis, riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse hallatava asutuse t&ouml;&ouml;taja ega kuuluda kohaliku omavalitsuse osalusega &auml;ri&uuml;hingu juhtorganisse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A rural municipality or city mayor shall not hold any other state or local government office, be employed by any agency under the administration of the state or a local government, or belong to directing bodies of companies with local government participation. </inglise>
<eesti>Ta on kohustatud viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast valimistulemuste kinnitamist teavitama enda valimisest asutust, kus ta on antud hetkel teenistuses v&otilde;i omab t&ouml;&ouml;lepingut. </eesti>
<inglise>A rural municipality or city mayor is required to notify the agency where he or she is in the service at the given moment or with which he or she has an employment contract of his or her election within five working days after the election results are approved. </inglise>
<eesti>Tema t&ouml;&ouml;leping l&otilde;petatakse t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32; 1998, 111, 1829; 1999, 16, 276; 60, 616; 2000, 25, 144; 51, 327; 57, 370; 102, 669; 2001, 17, 78; 42, 233; 53, 311) &sect; 85 alusel v&otilde;i ta vabastatakse ametist avaliku teenistuse seaduse &sect; 127 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>An employment contract of a rural municipality or city mayor shall be terminated pursuant to &sect; 85 of the Employment Contracts Act (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32; 1998, 111, 1829; 1999, 16, 276; 60, 616; 2000, 25, 144; 51, 327; 57, 370; 102, 669; 2001, 17, 78; 42, 233; 53, 311), or he or she shall be released from office pursuant to &sect; 127 of the Public Service Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Istungi ja koosoleku protokoll </eesti>
<inglise>Minutes of sessions and meetings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu istungi protokollile kirjutab alla volikogu esimees v&otilde;i tema asendaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Minutes of council sessions shall be signed by the chairman of the council or his or her deputy. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse istungi protokollile kirjutavad alla vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea v&otilde;i nende asendaja ja protokollija. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Minutes of rural municipality or city government sessions shall be signed by the rural municipality or city mayor or his or her deputy, and the secretary. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Volikogu v&otilde;i valitsuse komisjoni koosoleku protokollile kirjutab alla koosoleku juhataja. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Minutes of council or government committee meetings shall be signed by the chair of the meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Protokollile allakirjutanud isikud vastutavad protokollis sisalduvate andmete &otilde;igsuse eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Persons who sign minutes are responsible for the correctness of the information contained therein. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Protokolli kantakse istungi v&otilde;i koosoleku toimumise aeg ja koht, osav&otilde;tjate nimed, arutlusele tulevad k&uuml;simused, nende kohta esitatud ettepanekud ja vastuv&otilde;etud otsused, h&auml;&auml;letustulemused ning otsustajate v&otilde;i k&uuml;simuste algatajate eriarvamused. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The time and place of the session or meeting, names of participants, issues for discussion, proposals submitted and decisions passed pertaining thereto, voting results and dissenting opinions of persons who decided or initiated such issues shall be entered in the minutes. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Volikogu istungite protokollid peavad olema k&auml;ttesaadavad iga&uuml;hele. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Minutes of council sessions shall be accessible to everyone. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse istungite ning volikogu ja valitsuse komisjonide koosolekute protokollid peavad olema iga&uuml;hele k&auml;ttesaadavad valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Minutes of rural municipality and city government sessions and of meetings of council and government committees shall be accessible to everyone pursuant to the procedure provided for in the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) &Uuml;ldk&auml;ttesaadavaks ei tehta protokollides sisalduvaid andmeid, mille v&auml;ljastamine on seadusega piiratud v&otilde;i m&otilde;eldud valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuste siseseks kasutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Data contained in the minutes the issue of which is restricted by law or which is intended only for the internal use of rural municipality or city agencies shall not be made accessible to the public. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Protokollid ja teised dokumendid peavad vastama haldusdokumentidele kehtestatud p&otilde;hin&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Minutes and other documentation shall conform to the basic requirements established for administrative documents. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu tegutsemisv&otilde;imetus </eesti>
<inglise>Inability of council to act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Volikogu on tegutsemisv&otilde;imetu, kui ta: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A council is unable to act if it: </inglise>
<eesti>1) pole vastu v&otilde;tnud valla v&otilde;i linna eelarvet kolme kuu jooksul eelarveaasta algusest v&otilde;i riigieelarve vastuv&otilde;tmisest arvates, kui riigieelarvet ei olnud vastu v&otilde;etud eelarveaasta alguseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) fails to pass the rural municipality or city budget within three months after the beginning of the budgetary year or after passage of the state budget if the state budget is not passed as of the beginning of the budgetary year; </inglise>
<eesti>2) pole kahe kuu jooksul uue koosseisu esimese istungi kokkutulemise p&auml;evast arvates valinud volikogu esimeest ja vallavanemat v&otilde;i linnapead v&otilde;i pole nelja kuu jooksul uue koosseisu esimese istungi kokkutulemise p&auml;evast arvates kinnitanud valitsuse liikmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) fails to elect the chairman of the council, or the rural municipality or city mayor within two months after the date of the convention of the first council session or fails to confirm the membership of the government within four months after the date on which the first council session of the new membership is convened; </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>3) pole kahe kuu jooksul volikogu esimehe, vallavanema v&otilde;i linnapea ametist vabastamisest arvates valinud uut volikogu esimeest, vallavanemat v&otilde;i linnapead v&otilde;i pole nelja kuu jooksul vallavanema v&otilde;i linnapea vabastamisest arvates kinnitanud valitsuse liikmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) fails to elect a new chairman of the council, or a rural municipality or city mayor within two months after the release from office of the previous chairman of the council or the rural municipality or city mayor, or fails to confirm the membership of the government within four months after the release from office of the rural municipality or city mayor; </inglise>
<eesti>4) pole kahe kuu jooksul vallavanemale, linnapeale v&otilde;i valitsusele umbusalduse avaldamise p&auml;evast arvates valinud uut vallavanemat v&otilde;i linnapead ja pole nelja kuu jooksul umbusalduse avaldamise p&auml;evast arvates kinnitanud valitsuse liikmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>4) fails to elect a new rural municipality or city mayor within two months after the date of the expression of no confidence in the previous rural municipality or city mayor, or the government or fails to confirm the membership of the government within four months after the date of the expression of no confidence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui volikogu osutub tegutsemisv&otilde;imetuks, loetakse k&otilde;igi tema liikmete volitused ennet&auml;htaegselt l&otilde;ppenuks ning nende asemele astuvad asendusliikmed k&auml;esoleva seaduse Paragrahvis 20 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a council is unable to act, the authority of every council member is deemed to be prematurely terminated and alternate members shall replace them pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 20 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellisel juhul kutsub volikogu istungi kokku ja seda juhatab kuni volikogu esimehe valimiseni valla v&otilde;i linna valimiskomisjoni esimees v&otilde;i tema asendaja. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the council shall call a session which shall be chaired by the chairman or deputy chairman of the election committee of the rural municipality or city until the chairman of the council is elected. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui volikogu muutub tegutsemisv&otilde;imetuks v&auml;hem kui kuus kuud enne kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogude korralisi valimisi ning volikogu liikmete kohtade t&auml;itmiseks ei piisa volikogu asendusliikmeid, otsustab k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 22 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 13 ja 2. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud k&uuml;simusi valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a council loses its ability to act less than six months prior to local government council regular elections and the number of alternate council members is insufficient for the replacement of council members, the government shall decide on the issues set out in clause 22 (1) 13) and subsection 22 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. (Kehtetu - 30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. (Repealed - 30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>VII peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsusteenistuse p&otilde;hialused </eesti>
<inglise>General Principles of Local Government Service </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsusteenistus </eesti>
<inglise>Local government service </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Omavalitsusteenistust valla ja linna ametiasutustes reguleerib avalikku teenistust k&auml;sitlev seadus ja k&auml;esolev seadus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Local government service in rural municipality and city administrative agencies is regulated by the Act concerning public service and this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vallavanem ja linnapea ning nende abid, samuti valla- ja linnasekret&auml;r peavad valdama eesti keelt k&otilde;nes ja kirjas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Rural municipality and city mayors and their assistants and rural municipality and city secretaries must have oral and written proficiency in Estonian. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogu poolt valitud ja ametisse nimetatud isikute sotsiaalsed garantiid </eesti>
<inglise>Social guarantees for persons elected or appointed by council </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Palgalisel ametikohal t&ouml;&ouml;tavale volikogu esimehele v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itjale, vallavanemale v&otilde;i linnapeale ja volikogu poolt ametisse nimetatud valitsuse liikmele v&otilde;ib volikogu otsusega maksta ametist vabastamisel h&uuml;vitust kuni kolme kuu ametipalga ulatuses, kui ta on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud kaks kuni kaheksa aastat, ja kuni kuue kuu ametipalga ulatuses, kui ta on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud vastaval ametikohal rohkem kui kaheksa aastat ning vabastamine toimub: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The chairman of a council, his or her deputy, a rural municipality or city mayor, or a member of the government appointed by a council, working in a remunerative position, may be paid, in the event of his or her release from office, compensation by a decision of the council in the amount of up to three months' salary if the person has worked for two to eight years, and in the amount of up to six months' salary if the person has worked in the corresponding office for more than eight years, and the person is released from office: </inglise>
<eesti>seoses volituste t&auml;htajalise l&otilde;ppemisega; </eesti>
<inglise>due to the premature termination of his or her authority; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tema enda algatusel seoses terviseseisundiga, mis ei v&otilde;imalda p&uuml;sivalt oma teenistuskohustusi t&auml;ita; </eesti>
<inglise>2) on his or her own initiative due to his or her state of health which does not allow the performance of functions in a continuous manner; </inglise>
<eesti>3) seoses umbusalduse avaldamisega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) due to an expression of no confidence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud h&uuml;vitust ei maksta, kui volikogu poolt ametisse valitud v&otilde;i nimetatud isik: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The compensation provided for in subsection (1) of this section is not paid if the person elected or appointed by the council: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vabastatakse ametist tema enda algatusel, v.a k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 2 toodud juhul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) is released from office on his or her own initiative except in the case set out in clause (1) 2) of this section; </inglise>
<eesti>2) valitakse v&otilde;i nimetatakse volikogu poolt ametisse uueks t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) is elected or appointed for a new term of office by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>Valla- ja linnasekret&auml;r </eesti>
<inglise>Rural municipality and city secretaries </inglise>
<eesti>Valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;ri nimetab ametisse ja vabastab ametist seaduses s&auml;testatud korras vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea. </eesti>
<inglise>A rural municipality or city secretary is appointed to and released from office by the rural municipality or city mayor pursuant to the procedure provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;riks v&otilde;ib nimetada v&auml;hemalt 21-aastase Eesti kodaniku, kellel on juristi kvalifikatsioon v&otilde;i tunnistus Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud kutsen&otilde;uetele vastavuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Estonian citizens of at least 21 years of age who are qualified as jurists or hold a certificate of compliance with the professional qualification requirements established by the Government of the Republic may be appointed as rural municipality and city secretaries. </inglise>
<eesti>Valla- ja linnasekret&auml;ride vastavust kehtestatud kutsen&otilde;uetele kontrollib ja sellekohaseid tunnistusi annab v&auml;lja Vabariigi Valitsuse moodustatud valla- ja linnasekret&auml;ride kutsekomisjon. </eesti>
<inglise>The compliance of rural municipality and city secretaries with professional qualification requirements is supervised and certificates of compliance are issued by the Rural Municipality and City Secretaries Professional Qualifications Committee established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r ei kuulu valitsuse koosseisu, kuid ta v&otilde;tab s&otilde;na&otilde;igusega osa valitsuse istungitest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A rural municipality or city secretary does not belong to the membership of the government, however, he or she participates in government sessions with the right to speak. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;r: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A rural municipality or city secretary shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juhib valla- v&otilde;i linnakantseleid ning esitab vallavanemale v&otilde;i linnapeale ettepanekuid valla- v&otilde;i linnakantselei &uuml;lesannete, struktuuri ja teenistujate koosseisu kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) direct the office of the rural municipality or city and make proposals to the rural municipality or city mayor concerning the functions, structure and staff of public servants of the office of the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>2) annab kaasallkirja valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rustele ja korraldustele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) co-sign government regulations and orders; </inglise>
<eesti>3) korraldab valitsuse &otilde;igusaktide avaldamist ja t&ouml;&ouml; avalikustamist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) manage the publication of the legislation of the government and the disclosure of the activities of the government; </inglise>
<eesti>4) korraldab volikogu &otilde;igusaktide avaldamist ja t&ouml;&ouml; avalikustamist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) manage the publication of the legislation of the council and the disclosure of the activities of the council; </inglise>
<eesti>5) saadab &otilde;iguskantslerile valla v&otilde;i linna &otilde;igustloovate aktide &auml;rakirjad 10 p&auml;eva jooksul nende vastuv&otilde;tmisest arvates; </eesti>
<inglise>5) forward copies of rural municipality or city legislation of general application within ten days after their passage to the Legal Chancellor; </inglise>
<eesti>6) esindab valda v&otilde;i linna kohtus v&otilde;i volitab selleks teisi isikuid; </eesti>
<inglise>6) represent the rural municipality or city in the courts or authorise other persons to do so; </inglise>
<eesti>7) hoiab valla v&otilde;i linna vapipitsatit; </eesti>
<inglise>7) hold the public seal of the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>8) osaleb valitsuse istungite ettevalmistamisel ja korraldab istungite protokollimist; </eesti>
<inglise>8) participate in the preparation of government sessions and arrange the taking of minutes of sessions; </inglise>
<eesti>9) annab valla- v&otilde;i linnakantselei sisemise t&ouml;&ouml; korraldamiseks k&auml;skkirju; </eesti>
<inglise>9) issue directives for the organisation of the internal operations of the office of the rural municipality or city; </inglise>
<eesti>9 (1)) registreerib kriminaalmenetluse koodeksi (ENSV &Uuml;T 1961, 1, 4 ja lisa; RT I 2000, 56, 369; 75, &otilde;iend; 84, 533; 86, 542; 2001, 3, 9; 53, 306 ja 313; 56, 333; 65, 378) &sect;-s 129 s&auml;testatud juhul uurija kirjaliku m&auml;&auml;ruse alusel vallavanema v&otilde;i linnapea teenistussuhte peatumise m&auml;&auml;ruse saamisele j&auml;rgnevast t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>9 (1)) register, in the case specified in &sect; 129 of the Criminal Code (ENSV &Uuml;T (2) 1961, 1, 4 and Annex; RT I 2000, 56, 369; 75, correction notice; 84, 533; 86, 542; 2001, 3, 9; 53, 306 and 313; 56, 333; 65, 378), the suspension of an employment contract of a rural municipality or city mayor based on the written order by a preliminary investigator as of the working day following receipt of the order; </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>10) t&auml;idab teisi seaduses, valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses ja valitsuse t&ouml;&ouml;korras pandud &uuml;lesandeid. </eesti>
<inglise>10) perform other functions assigned to him or her pursuant to law, the statutes of the rural municipality or city, and the rules of procedure of the government. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;ri asendamise korra m&auml;&auml;rab vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The procedure for the substitution of a rural municipality or city secretary is determined by the rural municipality or city mayor. </inglise>
<eesti>Valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;ri asendajal on k&otilde;ik valla- v&otilde;i linnasekret&auml;ri &otilde;igused ja kohustused ning ta peab vastama k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>A substitute for a rural municipality or city secretary has all the rights and obligations of a rural municipality or city secretary and he or she shall comply with the requirements provided for in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99, teine lause j&otilde;ustub 01.01.2002, - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99, second sentence enters into force 01.01.2002, - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>VIII peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Osavalla ja linnaosa moodustamine ning t&ouml;&ouml;korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Formation and Procedure of Rural Municipality and City Districts </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Osavald ja linnaosa </eesti>
<inglise>Rural municipality or city district </inglise>
<eesti>Osvald v&otilde;i linnaosa on valla v&otilde;i linna maa-alal ja koosseisus volikogu poolt kinnitatud osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruse alusel tegutsev &uuml;ksus. </eesti>
<inglise>A rural municipality or city district is a unit which operates in the territory and within the composition of a rural municipality or city pursuant to the statutes of the rural municipality or city district approved by the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>Osavalla ja linnaosa moodustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Formation of rural municipality or city district </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa moodustamise v&otilde;ivad algatada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The formation of a rural municipality or city district may be initiated by: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;ks neljandik volikogu liikmetest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) one fourth of the members of the council; </inglise>
<eesti>2) taotluse korras v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks protsent h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguslikest valla- v&otilde;i linnaelanikest, kuid mitte v&auml;hem kui viis h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;iguslikku valla- v&otilde;i linnaelanikku; </eesti>
<inglise>2) not less than one per cent of the residents of the rural municipality or city with the right to vote, however not less than five residents with the right to vote, by way of an application; </inglise>
<eesti>3) valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the rural municipality or city government. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The statutes of a rural municipality or city district shall provide: </inglise>
<eesti>(27.09.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.09.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 82, 498) </inglise>
<eesti>1) osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa piiride kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a description of the boundaries of the rural municipality or city district; </inglise>
<eesti>2) osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa valitsuse moodustamise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the procedure for formation of the government of the rural municipality or city district; </inglise>
<eesti>3) osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa vanema ametisse nimetamise kord, kusjuures vanema volituste t&auml;htaeg ei tohi &uuml;letada antud valla v&otilde;i linna volikogu volituste t&auml;htaega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the procedure for the appointment to office of the rural municipality or city district elder, whereby the term of authority of the rural municipality or city district elder shall not exceed the term of authority of the rural municipality or city council; </inglise>
<eesti>4) osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa valitsuse ja vanema volitused ning nende teostamiseks vajalikud antud valla v&otilde;i linna eelarvelised vahendid; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the authority of the rural municipality or city district government and rural municipality or city district elder and the budgetary funds of the rural municipality or city allocated for the performance thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>5) osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa valitsuse ja vanema tegevuse j&auml;relevalve ning osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa likvideerimise alused ja kord. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the bases and procedure for supervision over the activities of the rural municipality or city district government and the rural municipality or city district elder, and for liquidation of the rural municipality or city district. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Taotluse alusel otsustab volikogu osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa moodustamise v&otilde;i l&uuml;kkab taotluse tagasi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A council shall decide to form a rural municipality or city district on the basis of an application or shall refuse such application. </inglise>
<eesti>Vajaduse korral v&otilde;ib volikogu korraldada nimetatud k&uuml;simuses elanike k&uuml;sitluse. </eesti>
<inglise>The council may organise an opinion poll of the residents concerning such issue, if necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa valitsusel ja vanemal pole &otilde;igustloova akti andmise &otilde;igust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Rural municipality and city district governments and rural municipality and city district elders do not have the right to pass legislation of general application. </inglise>
<eesti>(23.11.94 j&otilde;ust.12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.11.94 entered into force 12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa vanem v&otilde;ib oma volituste piires ja &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks anda &uuml;ksikaktina korraldusi ning valitsuse sisemise t&ouml;&ouml; korraldamiseks k&auml;skkirju. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Rural municipality and city district elders may, within the limits of their authority and for the performance of their functions, issue orders as legislation of specific application and directives for the organisation of the internal operations of the government. </inglise>
<eesti>(23.11.94 j&otilde;ust.12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.11.94 entered into force 12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa vanema korraldustele kohaldatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 31 1.-5. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The requirements provided for in subsections 31 (1) -(5) of this Act apply to orders issued by rural municipality and city district elders. </inglise>
<eesti>Korraldusele kirjutab alla osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa vanem. </eesti>
<inglise>Orders shall be signed by the rural municipality or city district elder. </inglise>
<eesti>(23.11.94 j&otilde;ust.12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.11.94 entered into force 12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa vanema korralduste &uuml;le teostab kontrolli vallavanem v&otilde;i linnapea valla v&otilde;i linna p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Supervision over orders issued by a rural municipality or city district elder is exercised by the rural municipality or city mayor pursuant to the procedure provided for in the statutes of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(23.11.94 j&otilde;ust.12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.11.94 entered into force 12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Valla v&otilde;i linna eelarveaasta jooksul ei tohi piirata osavalla v&otilde;i linnaosa valitsuse ja vanema volitusi ega v&auml;hendada neile eraldatud eelarvelisi vahendeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The authority of rural municipality and city district governments and rural municipality and city district elders shall not be restricted and budgetary funds allocated to them shall not be decreased during the budgetary year of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>Aleviku- ja k&uuml;lavanem </eesti>
<inglise>Small town and village elders </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Aleviku v&otilde;i k&uuml;la koosolekul v&otilde;idakse valida aleviku- v&otilde;i k&uuml;lavanem. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A small town or village elder may be elected by the small town or village meeting. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vallavalitsuse &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine aleviku- v&otilde;i k&uuml;lavanema poolt s&auml;testatakse lepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The performance of tasks of a rural municipality government by a small town or village elder shall be provided for in a contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Aleviku- v&otilde;i k&uuml;lavanema volituste kestus ei ole piiratud volikogu volituste kestusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The term of authority of a small town or village elder shall not be restricted by the term of authority of the council. </inglise>
<eesti>IX peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Maakogu </eesti>
<inglise>County Assembly </inglise>
<eesti>(Kehtetu - 23.11.94 j&otilde;ust.12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </eesti>
<inglise>(Repealed - 23.11.94 entered into force 12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </inglise>
<eesti>X peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 10 </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste koost&ouml;&ouml; </eesti>
<inglise>Co-operation of Local Governments </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 62. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 62. </inglise>
<eesti>Koost&ouml;&ouml;vormid </eesti>
<inglise>Forms of co-operation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vallad ja linnad v&otilde;ivad &uuml;histe huvide v&auml;ljendamiseks, esindamiseks ja kaitsmiseks ning &uuml;histe &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the expression, representation and protection of common interests and for the performance of common functions, rural municipalities and cities may: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tegutseda &uuml;hiselt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) co-operate; </inglise>
<eesti>2) anda sellekohased volitused m&otilde;nele vallale v&otilde;i linnale; </eesti>
<inglise>2) grant authority to another rural municipality or city for this purpose; </inglise>
<eesti>3) moodustada omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liite. </eesti>
<inglise>3) form local government associations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes t&auml;hendatud koost&ouml;&ouml; korral v&otilde;ivad vallad ja linnad n&auml;ha lepinguga ette &uuml;hisasutuste moodustamise. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of co-operation specified in subsection (1) of this section, rural municipalities and cities may found joint agencies on the basis of a contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 63. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 63. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liidu asutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Foundation of local government associations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liidu asutamise aluseks on omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste vahel s&otilde;lmitud asutamisleping ja ta tegutseb seaduse ja registreeritud p&otilde;hikirja alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The basis for formation of a local government association is a foundation agreement between local governments; an association of local governments shall operate pursuant to law and its registered articles of association. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liidu p&otilde;hikirjas s&auml;testatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The articles of association of a local government association shall provide: </inglise>
<eesti>1) liidu nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and address of the association; </inglise>
<eesti>2) liidu liikmed; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the members of the association; </inglise>
<eesti>3) liidu &uuml;lesanded; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the functions of the association; </inglise>
<eesti>4) liidu organid; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the bodies of the association; </inglise>
<eesti>5) liidu esinduskogu ja teiste organite esindusnormid ning h&auml;&auml;letamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the principles of representation and voting of the representative body and other bodies of the association; </inglise>
<eesti>6) liidu organite volitused; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the authority of the bodies of the association; </inglise>
<eesti>7) liikmemaksude kehtestamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tted ja liidu liikmete osalus liidu vara soetamisel ja kasutamisel ning liidu v&otilde;lgade tasumisel; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the principles for the establishment of membership fees and participation of the members of the association in the procurement and use of the property of the association and payment of the debts thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>8) uute liikmete vastuv&otilde;tmise ja liidust v&auml;ljaastumise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>8) the procedure for confirmation of new members and resignation of members from the association; </inglise>
<eesti>9) p&otilde;hikirja muutmise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>9) the procedure for amendment of the articles of association; </inglise>
<eesti>10) liidu tegevuse revideerimise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>10) the procedure for auditing the activities of the association; </inglise>
<eesti>11) liidu likvideerimise alused ja kord. </eesti>
<inglise>11) the bases and procedure for liquidation of the association. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 64. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 64. </inglise>
<eesti>Lepingud riigiorganitega </eesti>
<inglise>Contracts with state bodies </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liidu esinduskogul v&otilde;i tema volitusel m&otilde;nel teisel liidu organil on &otilde;igus s&otilde;lmida liidu nimel lepinguid riigi valitsusasutustega riikliku kohustuse t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The representative body of a local government association or, upon its authorisation, other bodies of the association have the right to enter into contracts in the name of such association with state government agencies for the performance of state obligations. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riiklikke kohustusi v&otilde;tab omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liit t&auml;itmiseks juhul, kui selle poolt on k&otilde;ik liitu kuuluvad volikogud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A local government association undertakes to perform state obligations if all councils belonging to the association are in favour thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>XI peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 11 </inglise>
<eesti>Suhted riigiorganitega ja j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Relations with State Bodies and Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(23.11.94 j&otilde;ust.12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.11.94 entered into force 12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 65. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 65. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse suhted riigiorganitega </eesti>
<inglise>Relations between local governments and state bodies </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kohalike omavalitsusorganite ning riigi valitsusasutuste suhted p&otilde;hinevad seadusel ja lepingul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Relations between local government bodies and state government agencies are based on law and contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohalikud omavalitsusorganid ei tohi delegeerida oma &uuml;lesandeid ja p&auml;devust ning nende t&auml;itmiseks seadusega etten&auml;htud vahendeid riigi valitsusasutustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Local government bodies shall not delegate their functions, competence or funds allocated to them pursuant to law for the performance thereof to state government agencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(23.11.94 j&otilde;ust.12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </eesti>
<inglise>(23.11.94 entered into force 12.12.94 - RT I 1994, 84, 1475) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Valla v&otilde;i linna volikogul on &otilde;igus esitada Vabariigi Valitsusele ettepanekuid seaduste ning teiste &otilde;igusaktide vastuv&otilde;tmiseks v&otilde;i muutmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Rural municipality and city councils have the right to submit proposals to the Government of the Republic for the passage or amendment of Acts and other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kohalike v&otilde;imuorganitega konsulteeritakse &otilde;igeaegselt ja sobival viisil k&otilde;igi neid otseselt puudutavate k&uuml;simuste planeerimise ja otsustamise puhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Local executive bodies are consulted in a timely and appropriate manner in the planning and resolution of issues which directly pertain to the bodies. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 66. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 66. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohaliku omavalitsuse tegevuse j&auml;relevalve ja kontroll </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision and inspection of local government activities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Maavanem teostab j&auml;relevalvet kohaliku omavalitsuse tegevuse &uuml;le seadusega s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The county governor exercises supervision over the activities of local government pursuant to the procedure provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Valla v&otilde;i linna valdusse antud riigivara kasutamist ja k&auml;sutamist kontrollib Riigikontroll vastavalt oma p&auml;devusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The State Audit Office inspects, within the limits of its competence, the use and disposal of state assets transferred to the possession of rural municipalities and cities. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) J&auml;relevalvet valla v&otilde;i linna &otilde;igustloovate aktide vastavuse &uuml;le Eesti Vabariigi p&otilde;hiseadusele ja seadustele teostab &otilde;iguskantsler. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Legal Chancellor exercises supervision over the conformity of the legislation of general application of rural municipalities and cities with the Constitution of the Republic of Estonia and law. </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 66 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 66 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Teenistuslik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Supervisory control </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Teenistuslik j&auml;relevalve on valitsuse poolt valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuste ja nende ametiisikute ning ametiasutuste hallatavate asutuste ja nende juhtide tegevuse seaduslikkuse ja otstarbekuse &uuml;le teostatav kontroll. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Supervisory control is control exercised by the government over the legality and purposefulness of the activities of rural municipality and city administrative agencies and of their officials, and of the agencies under the administration of rural municipality and city administrative agencies and of their managers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistusliku j&auml;relevalve teostamisel on valitsusel &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the exercise of supervisory control, the government has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teha ettekirjutus akti v&otilde;i toimingu puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) issue a precept for the elimination of deficiencies in a legal instrument or act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) peatada toimingu sooritamine v&otilde;i akti kehtivus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) suspend the performance of an act or the validity of a legal instrument; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tunnistada akt kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise>3) invalidate a legal instrument. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Teenistusliku j&auml;relevalve korras tehtud otsused peavad olema motiveeritud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Resolutions passed by way of supervisory control shall be reasoned. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuse ja nende ametiisikute ning ametiasutuse hallatava asutuse juhi akti t&auml;itmise ja toimingu v&otilde;ib peatada kuni k&uuml;mneks t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks akti v&otilde;i toimingu seaduslikkuse ja otstarbekuse t&auml;iendavaks kontrollimiseks v&otilde;i vajalike t&auml;iendavate andmete kogumiseks, sealhulgas akti andja v&otilde;i toimingu sooritaja selgituste saamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The implementation of a legal instrument or performance of an act of a rural municipality or city administrative agency and of their official, and of the manager of an agency under the administration of a rural municipality or city administrative agency may be suspended for up to ten working days for the supplementary control of the legality and purposefulness of the legal instrument or act, or for the collection of necessary supplementary information, including explanations from the issuer of the legal instrument or the performer of the act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Akti t&auml;itmise v&otilde;i toimingu sooritamise peatamisel teenistusliku j&auml;relevalve korras peatub seaduse ning nende alusel ja t&auml;itmiseks antud &otilde;igusaktidega vastava toimingu sooritamiseks kehtestatud t&auml;htaja kulgemine. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the suspension of the implementation of a legal instrument or the performance of an act by way of supervisory control, the running of the period established by law, or legislation issued for implementation on the basis thereof, or other legislation for the performance of a given act shall be suspended. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Valitsus tunnistab kehtetuks valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuste ning nende ametiisikute ja ametiasutuste hallatavate asutuste juhtide akte ja toiminguid, mis ei ole vastavuses Eesti Vabariigi p&otilde;hiseaduse, seaduste ning nende alusel ja t&auml;itmiseks antud &otilde;igusaktide ning valla v&otilde;i linna &otilde;igusaktidega. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The government shall repeal a legal instrument or act of the rural municipality or city government administrative agency and of their official, and of the manager of an agency under the administration of a rural municipality or city administrative agency which is not in conformity with the Constitution of the Republic of Estonia, other laws, or legislation issued for implementation on the basis thereof, or rural municipality or city legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Valitsus tunnistab ebaotstarbekuse motiivil kehtetuks valla v&otilde;i linna ametiasutuste ning nende ametiisikute ja ametiasutuste hallatavate asutuste juhtide akte ja toiminguid juhul, kui akt v&otilde;i toiming ilmselt ei vasta kohaliku omavalitsuse p&otilde;him&otilde;tetele v&otilde;i p&otilde;hjustab valla- v&otilde;i linnavara ja eelarveliste vahendite ebaratsionaalset kasutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The government shall invalidate a legal instrument or an act of the rural municipality or city government administrative agency and of their official, and of the manager of an agency under the administration of a rural municipality or city administrative agency on the grounds of lack of purposefulness if the legal instrument or act is clearly not in conformity with the principles of the local government, or if it causes an unreasonable use of the assets or budget funds of the rural municipality or city. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Ebaotstarbekuse motiivil ei saa tunnistada kehtetuks akte ja toiminguid, mille andmise tingimused tulenevad seadusest ning nende alusel ja t&auml;itmiseks antud &otilde;igusaktidest. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Legal instruments and acts for which the conditions for issuance are provided by law, or legislation issued for implementation on the basis thereof, shall not be repealed or invalidated on the grounds of lack of purposefulness. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) K&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel ei teostata teenistuslikku j&auml;relevalvet haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustiku (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 453; 87, 524 ja 526; 97, 605; 102, 677) paragrahvides 189-216 s&auml;testatud ametiisikute aktide ja toimingute &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) Supervisory control on the basis of this Act is not exercised over the legal instruments issued and acts performed by the officials provided for in sections 189-216 of the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 2001, 74, 354; 87, 524 and 526; 97, 605; 102, 677). </inglise>
<eesti>(30.09.99 j&otilde;ust.15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </eesti>
<inglise>(30.09.99 entered into force 15.10.99 - RT I 1999, 75, 705) </inglise>
<eesti>XII peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 12 </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 67. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 67. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse j&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise>Entry into force of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse Riigi Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;evast j&otilde;ustuvad paragrahvid 1-5, 7, 10, 12-15, 23-26, 31, 33-37, 40-42, 50, 51, 56-58, 62-64 ja 66. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Sections 1-5, 7, 10, 12-15, 23-26, 31, 33-37, 40-42, 50, 51, 56-58, 62-64 and 66 of this Act enter into force as of the date of publication of this Act in the Riigi Teataja. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse paragrahv 55 2. l&otilde;ige j&otilde;ustub alates 1997.aasta 1. jaanuarist. </eesti>
<inglise>Subsection 55 (2) of this Act enters into force as of 1 January 1997. </inglise>
<eesti>Teised seaduse paragrahvid j&otilde;ustuvad k&auml;esoleva seaduse vastuv&otilde;tmisele j&auml;rgnevate kohalike omavalitsuste volikogude valimiste tulemuste v&auml;ljakuulutamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>Other sections of this Act enter into force as of the date of the announcement of the results of the first local government council elections following the passage of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui kohaliku omavalitsuse volikogu valimised on j&auml;&auml;nud m&otilde;nes omavalitsus&uuml;ksuses toimumata v&otilde;i valimistulemused v&auml;lja kuulutamata, valitakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvi 59 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud maakonna omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse esindaja maakogusse volikogu eelmise koosseisu poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If elections to a local government council do not take place or the election results are not announced, a representative of the local government of the county to the county assembly specified in subsection 59 (1) of this Act shall be elected by the previous membership of the council. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.03.94 j&otilde;ust.29.03.94 - RT I 1994, 19, 340) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.03.94 entered into force 29.03.94 - RT I 1994, 19, 340) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 68. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 68. </inglise>
<eesti>Alevite ja vabariiklike linnade staatus </eesti>
<inglise>Status of towns and independent cities </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisega saavad alevid valla staatuse ja vabariiklikud linnad linna staatuse. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the entry into force of this Act, towns obtain the status of rural municipalities and independent cities obtain the status of cities. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 69. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 69. </inglise>
<eesti>Volikogude volituste l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of authority of councils </inglise>
<eesti>Valla-, alevi-, linna- ja maavolikogude k&auml;esoleva koosseisu ja nende liikmete volitused l&otilde;pevad seaduse j&otilde;ustumisele j&auml;rgnevate kohalike omavalitsuste volikogude valimiste tulemuste v&auml;ljakuulutamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>The authority of the current memberships and members of rural municipality, town, city and county councils terminates on the date the results of the first local government council elections following the entry into force of this Act are announced. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 70. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 70. </inglise>
<eesti>Maavanemate ja maavalitsuste volituste aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Term of authority of county governors and county governments </inglise>
<eesti>Maavolikogude k&auml;esoleva koosseisu poolt ametisse kinnitatud maavanemate, abimaavanemate ja maavalitsuse n&otilde;unike volitused l&otilde;pevad seaduse j&otilde;ustumisele j&auml;rgnevate kohalike omavalitsuste volikogude valimiste tulemuste v&auml;ljakuulutamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>The authority of county governors, assistant county governors and counsellors to county governments the appointment to office of whom was confirmed by the current memberships of the county councils terminates on the date the results of the first local government council elections following the entry into force of this Act are announced. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 71. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 71. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rused </eesti>
<inglise>Statutes of local governments </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rused tuleb kinnitada v&otilde;i viia koosk&otilde;lla k&auml;esoleva seadusega kolme kuu jooksul j&auml;rgmiste kohalike omavalitsuste volikogude valimiste tulemusena moodustatud volikogude poolt valla- v&otilde;i linnavalitsuse ametisse kinnitamise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>The statutes of local governments shall be approved or brought into accordance with this Act within three months from the date that the appointment to office of the rural municipality or city government is confirmed by the council formed as a result of the next elections. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 72. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 72. </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liitude p&otilde;hikirjad </eesti>
<inglise>Articles of association of local government associations </inglise>
<eesti>Enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse vastuv&otilde;tmist moodustatud omavalitsuste liitude p&otilde;hikirjad tuleb kolme kuu jooksul viia koosk&otilde;lla k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 63 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetega. </eesti>
<inglise>The articles of association of local government associations which were formed prior to the entry into force of this Act shall be brought into accordance with the requirements provided for in subsection 63 (2) of this Act within three months. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 72 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 72 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liidu &uuml;mberregistreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of local government association </inglise>
<eesti>Eesti Vabariigi ettev&otilde;tete, asutuste ja organisatsioonide registris registreeritud kohalike omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste liidud kuuluvad &uuml;mberregistreerimisele 2002. aasta 1. oktoobriks. </eesti>
<inglise>Local government associations registered in the register of enterprises, agencies and organisations of the Republic of Estonia shall be re-registered by 1 October 2002. </inglise>
<eesti>(13.06.2000 j&otilde;ust.10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 322) </eesti>
<inglise>(13.06.2000 entered into force 10.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 51, 322) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 73. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 73. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igusaktide kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Repeal of legislation </inglise>
<eesti>Eesti N&otilde;ukogude Sotsialistliku Vabariigi kohaliku omavalitsuse aluste seadus (ENSV Teataja 1989, 34, 517) ja Eesti Vabariigi 1991.aasta 21.augusti seadus "Eesti NSV kohaliku omavalitsuse aluste seaduse osalise muutmise kohta" (RT 1991, 27, 324) tunnistatakse kehtetuks k&auml;esoleva seaduse vastuv&otilde;tmisele j&auml;rgnevate kohalike omavalitsuste volikogude valimiste tulemuste v&auml;ljakuulutamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>The Estonian Soviet Socialist Republic Principles of Local Government Act (ENSV Teataja (3) 1989, 34, 517) and the Republic of Estonia Act "on Partial Amendment of the Estonian Soviet Socialist Republic Principles of Local Government Act" of 21 August 1991 (RT 1991, 27, 324) are repealed as of the date on which the results of the first local government council elections following the passage of this Act are announced. </inglise>
<eesti>Samast p&auml;evast tunnistatakse kehtetuks: </eesti>
<inglise>The following are repealed as of the same date: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ENSV &Uuml;lemn&otilde;ukogu Presiidiumi 1989.aasta 6.detsembri seadlus "Omavalitsusliku halduss&uuml;steemi loomisest" (ENSV Teataja 1989, 40, 614); </eesti>
<inglise>1) Decree of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the ESSR of 6 December 1989 "on Creation of a System of Administration Based on Local Government" (ENSV Teataja 1989, 40, 614); </inglise>
<eesti>2) ENSV &Uuml;lemn&otilde;ukogu Presiidiumi 1990.aasta 22.jaanuari seadlus "Kohaliku omavalitsuse juhtivt&ouml;&ouml;tajate staatuse kohta" (Eesti Vabariigi Teataja 1990, 14, 236); </eesti>
<inglise>2) Decree of the Presidium of the Supreme Soviet of the ESSR of 22 January 1990 "on the Status of the Senior Officials of Local Government" (Eesti Vabariigi Teataja (4) 1990, 14, 236); </inglise>
<eesti>3) ENSV &Uuml;lemn&otilde;ukogu 1989.aasta 8.augusti otsus "Haldusreformi l&auml;biviimisest Eesti NSV-s" (ENSV Teataja 1989, 26, 348); </eesti>
<inglise>3) Resolution of the Supreme Soviet of the ESSR of 8 August 1989 "on the Implementation of Administrative Reform in the Estonian SSR" (ENSV Teataja 1989, 26, 348); </inglise>
<eesti>4) EV &Uuml;lemn&otilde;ukogu Presiidiumi 1991.aasta 11.juuli otsus "Omavalitsuslikku staatust taotlevate linna-, alevi- ja k&uuml;lan&otilde;ukogude p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;ruste ning arengukavade vastuv&otilde;tmise, registreerimise ja l&auml;bivaatamise kohta" (RT 1991, 24, 289). </eesti>
<inglise>4) Resolution of the Presidium of the Supreme Council of the Republic of Estonia of 11 July 1991" on the Acceptance, Registration and Review of Statutes and Development Plans of City, Town and Village Councils Applying for Local Government Status" (RT 1991, 24, 289). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 74. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 74. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastuolude lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Settlement of disparities </inglise>
<eesti>Vastuolu korral k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 67 loetletud s&auml;tete ja Eesti N&otilde;ukogude Sotsialistliku Vabariigi kohaliku omavalitsuse aluste seaduse ning teiste seaduste ja &otilde;igusaktide s&auml;tete vahel loetakse kehtivateks k&auml;esoleva seaduse s&auml;tted. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of disparities in the provisions specified in &sect; 67 of this Act and the Estonian Soviet Socialist Republic Principles of Local Government Act and provisions of other Acts and legislation, the provisions of this Act apply. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 75. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 75. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igusaktide koosk&otilde;lla viimine </eesti>
<inglise>Accordance of legislation The Government of the Republic shall submit proposals to bring Acts and other legislation into accordance with this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsus esitab ettepanekud seaduste ja teiste &otilde;igusaktide koosk&otilde;lla viimiseks k&auml;esoleva seadusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) RT = Riigi Teataja = State Gazette (2) ENSV &Uuml;T = ENSV &Uuml;lemn&otilde;ukogu Teataja = ESSR Supreme Council Gazette </inglise>


